    "id": "Team-Lead-UX-Design---Telematics_25619-1",
    "title": "Team Lead UX Design - Telematics",
    "description": "<span><p><span>What if we told you that you can achieve more at TomTom in less time than at any other company?</span></p><p></p><p><span>From coding the next product revolution, to selling it, we always want inspired people to join us. </span></p><p></p><p><span>Find the right vacancy for you? Please click Apply.<span>&nbsp;</span>We look forward getting to know you!</span></p></span><p></p><p><span>TomTom Telematics is one of the world’s leading telematics solution providers with more than 696,000 subscriptions worldwide. The company services drivers in more than 60 countries, giving them the industry’s strongest local support network and widest range of sector-specific third party applications and integrations. More than 46,000 customers benefit every day from the high standards of confidentiality, integrity and availability of our ISO/IEC 27001:2013 certified service</span><span>, re-audited in November 2016</span></p><p></p><p><b>Where do you want to be?</b></p><p>We are looking for the best and brightest minds in UX design to lead our team of highly skilled and creative engineers dedicated to delivering great new user experiences with outstanding levels of robustness and attention to detail, and committed to bringing those experiences to millions of users through a growing range of products and platforms.</p><p>Based in Leipzig, your tasks as an UX Team Lead will be</p><ul><li>Leading the UX design team, including motivating, developing as well as giving constructive feedback;</li><li>Conducting all aspects of performance management for your team;</li><li>Creating design concepts based on user insights, their unmet needs and emotions and on your understanding of technology constraints and opportunities;</li><li>Define UI and software behavior and analyze the benefits and challenges of different settings for users;</li><li>Interacting and working with Product Managers, Product Owners and other stakeholders on a permanent base.</li></ul><p></p><p><b>What do we expect from you?</b></p><p></p><p>There is no set route to become an UX Team Lead at TomTom. But to be successful in this role, this is the kind of profile we have in mind</p><ul><li>University degree in Interaction Design, HCI or comparable and several years of management experience;</li><li>A wizard in designing software applications for mobile, devices or web and expertise in usability engineering;</li><li>Skilled with a broad toolkit of Interaction Design tools, including sketching, prototyping, flow creation and basic animation, 3D experience is a bonus;</li><li>Strong portfolio with a variety of work in software user experience design;</li><li>Outstanding communication skills and very good leadership potential;</li><li>Fluent in German and English.</li></ul><p></p><p><b>What do we offer?</b></p><p></p><p>An adventure in software product development within a rapidly growing business unit of a globally renowned brand. After getting started with the WEBFLEET product landscape you will have various opportunities for your professional development. Being part of a team of expert developers and contribute in building and adapting technology for WEBFLEET, TomTom’s leading fleet management system. Indefinite contract, 30 annual leave days, child care policy, 100% employer funded pension plan, up to 50% discount on products, 15% bonus scheme. Among others, an online learning platform (1500 courses &amp; 11000 e-books) as well as live speeches from software development gurus, like Uncle Bob.</p><p></p><p><b>Who are we?</b></p><p></p><p>TomTom empowers movement. Every day millions of people around the world depend on TomTom to make smarter decisions. We design and develop innovative products that make it easy for people to keep moving towards their goals.</p><p></p><p>Our map-based components include map content, online map-based services, real-time traffic, and navigation software. Our consumer products include PNDs, navigation apps, and GPS sports watches. Our main business products are custom in-dash navigation systems and a fleet management system, which is offered to fleet owners as an online service with integrated in-vehicle cellular devices.</p><p>Our business consists of four customer facing business units: Consumer, Automotive, Maps and Telematics.</p><p></p><p>Founded in 1991 and headquartered in Amsterdam, we have 4,500 employees worldwide and sell our products in over 36 countries. For further information, please visit www.tomtom.com`</p><p></p><p><b>Interested?</b></p><p></p><p>For the full story about the vacancy or procedure, please click on <u>www.tomtom.com/careers</u> or for specific questions contact Jana Zaremba. We are looking forward to receive your application including design samples.</p><p></p><p>Online assessments and pre-employment screening are part of the selection process.</p>",
