    "title": "Interaction Designer",
    "description": "<span><p><span>What if we told you that you can achieve more at TomTom in less time than at any other company?</span></p><p></p><p><span>From coding the next product revolution, to selling it, we always want inspired people to join us. </span></p><p></p><p><span>Find the right vacancy for you? Please click Apply.<span>&nbsp;</span>We look forward getting to know you!</span></p></span><p>Where do you want to be…in a year, in 5 years?&nbsp;</p><p>What if you had the opportunity to achieve more in less time then you could ever imagine?</p><p>At TomTom, you can.</p><p>The TomTom Sports UX team is at the forefront of product design, usability and innovation in GPS enabled sports wearables and cameras. The UX team is responsible for a broad ecosystem of services and products including mobile and desktop apps as well as consumer electronics.</p><p>We have a position open in our Belgrade office for an exceptional Interaction Designer working closely with the local development team as well as designers, researchers and stakeholders based in 3 other countries. The Interaction Designer will specify detailed designs for implementation and create new feature concepts within an established eco-system.</p><p>They will apply a User Centered Design (UCD) methodology to understand users and their needs in order to create the most compelling solutions. Working with all relevant stakeholders to establish strategies that go beyond (or pre-cede) the project boundaries.</p><p><b>Sound good so far?</b></p><p><b>Here’s a little taste of your challenge:</b></p><ul><li>Has final responsibility for delivered product design aspects</li><li>Define and accurately document the functionality, navigation, interaction and information architecture in relation to the user needs and project constraints</li><li>Responsible for user analysis, interaction design, specification and development support</li><li>Create the best possible deliverable product user experience</li><li>Primary contact for all design issues within a busy development office</li><li>Work closely with lead designers, visual design and research teams</li><li>Responsible for the design process within projects and time estimations of design tasks</li><li>Present concepts and designs to the stakeholders and team members including a proper rationale</li><li>Drive interaction designs from conceptualization through prototyping to implementation with the project team</li><li>Assess the usability of existing designs or designs in development</li><li>Generate innovative and viable concepts to deliver products and influence the future roadmap</li><li>Effortlessly maintain a strong connection with the UX team across 4 countries and 9 different nationalities – including short visits to offices in London, Amsterdam and Edinburgh</li><li>Initially joining a project design team of two interaction designers, an art director and visual designers within the Sports UX department</li></ul><p><b>What we are looking for:</b></p><p>To be successful in this role, you will need a passion for great design and a holistic understanding of what makes great user experiences. Additionally you need:</p><ul><li>Outstanding portfolio that includes web, mobile and rich internet applications and demonstrates a history of working with consumer applications</li><li>University level qualification in Media &amp; Design, Human Computer Interaction or Industrial Design with 3-5 years of experience or higher professional level with 5-8 years of experience</li><li>Solid knowledge and ability to apply both quantitative and qualitative usability research methods</li><li>Experience with Adobe Creative Suite, Sketch or similar tools</li><li>An ability to demonstrate a strong understanding and interest in design processes, and user centric design</li><li>The ability to create interactive prototypes</li><li>A passion for communicating directly and through clear specifications with Agile development teams</li><li>Relentless attention to consistency and detail along with exceptional organizational, logical and analytical skills</li><li>Ability to solve complex problems and drive projects from concept to conclusion; manage multiple tasks, and set priorities with direction or feedback from management.</li><li>The ability to represent the UX department to internal and external stakeholders</li><li>Excellent time-management and prioritization skills with the ability to multi-task across projects;</li><li>Excellent teamwork and interpersonal communication skills</li><li>Fluent English (verbal, read, write) to allow seamless communication with an international team</li></ul><p><b>What you can expect</b></p><ul><li>You will never get bored! We move fast like a “start-up” but have the benefits of a billion euro company</li><li>A company culture that likes to work hard and play hard. We like to have fun. There is no sense coming to a job everyday if you don’t like the people you work with.</li><li>Have an idea? A suggestion? A new way of doing something? The founders are still very present in the company and are very accessible. We all are. There is always room for good ideas. Entrepreneurialism is valued.</li><li>Decisive actions. We don’t like to wait. It’s in our DNA to move forward. So it only makes sense that we don’t jam the company with lots of layers. We make things happen. Quickly.</li></ul><p><b>Want to join us?</b></p><p><b>We would like to meet you!</b></p><p>For the full story about the vacancy or procedure, please click on <a href=\"http://www.tomtom.com/careers\" target=\"_blank\">www.tomtom.com/careers</a> or contact Marta Brzeszczynska.</p><p>We kindly ask you to complete the form and attachments in English.</p><p>Pre-employment screening of all external candidates is part of the selection process.</p><p></p>",
