    "id": "Architect_25376",
    "title": "Architect",
    "description": "<span><p><span>What if we told you that you can achieve more at TomTom in less time than at any other company?</span></p><p></p><p><span>From coding the next product revolution, to selling it, we always want inspired people to join us. </span></p><p></p><p><span>Find the right vacancy for you? Please click Apply.<span>&nbsp;</span>We look forward getting to know you!</span></p></span><p>Our team <b>achieves more</b> every day. So can you.</p><p>We have been making Navigation apps since 2002 and have been the market leader ever since.<br>And we are not slowing down. &nbsp;<br><br>As the Architect for the Pipeline team within the Navigation Product Unit, you will define, drive and promote the technical strategy and architecture for the Continuous Integration &amp; Delivery Pipeline that underpins our agile software development process.</p><p>Our vision for the Delivery Pipeline is challenging and innovative, using the latest DevOps technology and design principles to provide a fast, scalable, reliable and cost-efficient Pipeline that enables TomTom development teams to deliver more, faster, to our customers.</p><p>The automotive industry is going through a massive period of technological change, and as the Pipeline Architect at TomTom you would be at the heart of helping to make it happen!</p><p><b>Sound interesting?</b></p><p>·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Are you good at designing cross-platform infrastructure &amp; describing it to others?</p><p>·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Are you always looking for ways to speed up delivery of great software to customers?</p><p>·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Can you promote the benefits &amp; principles of high quality DevOps infrastructure?</p><p>·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Do you like researching &amp; trying innovative DevOps and CI tools and techniques?</p><p>·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Do you enjoy teamwork and making things better; working with colleagues across multiple sites?</p><p></p><p>Then this is your ideal new job!</p><p><b>Here’s a little taste of your challenge</b></p><p>·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Own and design the Pipeline architecture that provides our future-proofed, highly automated solution for continuous integration &amp; delivery of Navigation software.</p><p>·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Provide technical leadership to the Pipeline team as they implement, monitor and maintain the Pipeline and emphasize the principles of a high quality “infrastructure as code” approach.</p><p>·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Make Pipeline infrastructure &amp; deployment design decisions based on economic analysis as well as new customer requirements or internal business needs.</p><p>·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Act as a subject matter expert on DevOps best practices throughout TomTom; on topics such as environment &amp; release automation, virtualization, use of Cloud services, monitoring &amp; auto-scaling</p><p>·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Perform analysis of emerging concepts &amp; tooling in DevOps and Infrastructure Automation to determine our future roadmap.</p><p>·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Provide thought leadership for your own innovations &amp; experience via participation in conferences or authoring white papers.</p><p>·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Help to define the software development processes &amp; codebase qualities that maximize efficient operation of the Pipeline</p><p>·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Review and audit of existing solution design and infrastructure architecture, including troubleshooting of identified problems.</p><p>·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Create technical documentation for Pipeline implementers, maintainers, operators and users.</p><p></p><p><b>What we expect from you</b></p><p>·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Strong background in Continuous Integration/Delivery</p><p>·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience in architecting cloud infrastructure such as: AWS, Azure, Openstack</p><p>·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Background in software development with predominantly C++ and Java</p><p>·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience in architecting designs and getting them developed / deployed, preferably in the Consumer Products, Automotive or Navigation industry</p><p>·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Ability to think out of the box and bring new ideas to the table</p><p>·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Up-to-date with the latest trends and development</p><p>·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Effective communication skills; to both technical and non-technical audiences</p><p>·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Excellent collaboration &amp; technical leadership skills; with both internal and external stakeholders</p><p>·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience in applying agile software engineering methods</p><p>·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; MSc or PhD degree in Software Engineering or Electronics/Electrical Engineering</p><p></p><p><b>What you can expect from us</b></p><p>·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; You will never get bored!&nbsp; We move fast like a “start-up” but have the benefits of a billion euro company.</p><p>·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A company culture that likes to work hard and play hard. We like to have fun. There is no sense coming to a job everyday if you don’t like the people you work with.</p><p>·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Have an idea? A suggestion? A new way of doing something?&nbsp; The founders are still very present in the company and are very accessible.&nbsp; We all are.&nbsp; There is always room for good ideas.&nbsp;</p><p>·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Let’s not forget the good stuff: flexible benefits (including multisport card), private medical care, 50% product discount and bonus scheme.</p><p>·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; ŁÓDŹ. A pretty cool city to live and work. Lots of inspiration and one of the future tech hubs of Europe!</p><p></p><p><b>Want to join us?</b></p><p>For the full story about the vacancy or procedure, please check in via www.tomtom.com/careers (nr ref: 25376) or contact Katarzyna Paczyńska</p><p>Online technical assessments and pre-employment screening are part of the selection process.Our team <b>achieves more</b> every day. So can you.</p>",
