    "id": "Associate-Manager-Communication_25327-1",
    "title": "Associate Manager Communication",
    "description": "<span><p><span>What if we told you that you can achieve more at TomTom in less time than at any other company?</span></p><p></p><p><span>From coding the next product revolution, to selling it, we always want inspired people to join us. </span></p><p></p><p><span>Find the right vacancy for you? Please click Apply.<span>&nbsp;</span>We look forward getting to know you!</span></p></span><p><b><i>'Five years from now we'll be active in areas we haven't yet dreamed of'</i>.<br>Harold Goddijn, CEO TomTom.</b></p><p>TomTom empowers movement. Every day millions of people around the world depend on TomTom to make smarter decisions. Would you like the opportunity to achieve more and contribute in forming the TomTom Pune story and communicate our mission?</p><p></p><p><b>Where do you want to be?</b></p><p>We are looking for an experienced communications professional to join our TomTom Pune team. This role is based in Pune, India and will be a good mix of internal and external communications through a wide range of channels, as well as stakeholder management, internally with TomTom Pune employees, global TomTom stakeholders and externally with media, potential TomTom candidates and partners in India. This role should ensure employees, potential new candidates and stakeholders of our organization are kept informed and motivated by the communications about our vibrant brand and company achievements. We have a great story and we want you to help us tell it.</p><p></p><p><b>The role requires: &nbsp;</b></p><ul><li>Formulating and implementing a holistic internal and external communications plan and adjust when required;</li><li>Ensuring that the communication strategy is aligned with the overarching company business objectives and &nbsp;(employer) brand strategy;</li><li>Ensuring &nbsp;that the communication plan includes all critical components of our human resource deliverables, site management strategy, innovation strategy and employer brand;</li><li>Managing internal communications output at site &amp; department level through a variety of channel – standalone publications, global intranet etc;</li><li>Driving awareness of the TomTom Pune employer brand internally and externally;</li><li>Alignment of all existing and new communication to an appealing standard keeping global guidelines into account;</li><li>Refining core messaging to ensure organizational consistency in all aspects of communications including development, organizing and education;</li><li>Tailoring (localized) key messages for specific target audiences;</li><li>Content development&nbsp; - blogs, whitepapers, local press releases;</li><li>Leading external communication initiatives such a thought leadership platforms, relevant speaker opportunities, forum and panel discussions Identifying, developing and maintaining strong media relationships;</li><li>Identify and manage the local PR, Social Media and digital activation agencies where applicable;</li><li>Handle the internal communication response to crisis situations which affect organizational perception and reputation together with crisis mgmt. team;</li><li>Work with your colleagues from TomTom Pune site management team, Actively Innovate team, external stakeholders and the Global Employer Brand and internal communications team in Amsterdam to optimize communication initiatives;</li><li>Ensure TomTom’s active, consistent representation on social media be it internal (Yammer) or external (on Glassdoor, Facebook, LinkedIn, portals etc) and in publications.</li></ul><p></p><p><b>Specific requirements: </b></p><p>Identify relevant information and channels to be communicated to employees? Edit, design and print corporate stories, local success stories, testimonials, white papers, presentations, scripts and messages; Content creation and marketing interventions; Publish content, photography and videos on internal and external Social Media; Identify value adding &nbsp;ATL/BTL campaigns and execute accordingly; Support ideas with background research and based on past experience; Event management; Set timing of release to coordinate with company events or initiatives; ‘Paid for” Media Planning; Work in collaboration with Marketing team for key deliverables.</p><p></p><p><b>What do we expect from you?</b></p><p>To manage these exciting tasks this is the kind of profile we have in mind:</p><ul><li>Minimum of&nbsp;8+ years relevant work experience required in external and internal communications preferably in an international company;</li><li>Demonstrated skills in developing communications strategy and tools from scratch;</li><li>Demonstrated skills in translating highly complex topics into a language accessible to everyone;</li><li>Mastering the digital world;</li><li>Demonstrated skills in the use of unconventional tools and technologies;</li><li>Can do attitude with marketing communication skills – track record required;</li><li>Excellent communication skills – written and verbal (English);</li><li>Good combination of analytical and creative capabilities, flexible, committed and passionate for the job;</li><li>Employer centric thinking, experience in implementing both locally developed campaigns and, implementing globally developed campaigns locally;</li><li>Demonstrated ease in a very diverse work environment;</li><li>Excellent interpersonal and relationship-building skills in order to work with all local and global employees &amp; stakeholders.</li></ul><p></p><p><b>What do we offer?</b></p><p>To be part of success:&nbsp; the TomTom Pune site is mainly focused on shaping the future of maps next to that services are being delivered to the global organization on consumer, IT, Finance and HR level; The chance to work in a fast moving, innovative and international environment, dealing with all kind of different countries and cultures; A world class market leading brand, a successful highly motivated team, with&nbsp;market leading products; Market rate salary &amp; benefits (depending on experience).</p><p></p><p><b>Who are we?</b></p><p>Our map-based components include map content, online map-based services, real-time traffic, and navigation software. Our consumer products include PNDs, navigation apps, and GPS sports watches. Our main business products are custom in-dash navigation systems and a fleet management system, which is offered to fleet owners as an online service with integrated in-vehicle cellular devices.</p><p>Our business consists of four customer facing business units: Consumer, Automotive, Licensing and Telematics.</p><p>Founded in 1991 and headquartered in Amsterdam, we have 4,500 employees worldwide and sell our products in over 38 countries. For further information, please visit&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.tomtom.com/\" target=\"_blank\">www.tomtom.com</a></p><p></p><p><b>Interested?</b></p><p>For the full story about the vacancy or procedure, please check tomtom.com/careers or contact Rosy Toms (rosy.toms@tomtom.com)</p><p>Pre-employment screening is part of the selection process. The candidate will be asked to share earlier published materials for reference reading.</p>",
