    "id": "Manager-Marketing-B2B---Telematics_JR0000026-1",
    "title": "Manager Marketing B2B - Telematics",
    "description": "<span><p><span>What if we told you that you can achieve more at TomTom in less time than at any other company?</span></p><p></p><p><span>From coding the next product revolution, to selling it, we always want inspired people to join us. </span></p><p></p><p><span>Find the right vacancy for you? Please click Apply.<span>&nbsp;</span>We look forward getting to know you!</span></p></span><p><b>Where do you want to be?</b></p><p></p><p>We are looking for the best and brightest minds in marketing to become part of our South African sales team. This position is a great opportunity for an experienced Marketer in a B2B environment who is looking to take his/her career to the next level. This role includes:</p><p>You will be responsible for developing a market plan and executing marketing in South Africa. &nbsp;This involves budget planning, strategy and the timely and qualitative execution of this plan. As a Marketing Manager you will report directly into the Sales Director South Africa.</p><ul><li>Develop, contribute and manage marketing activities with the TomTom Telematics resellers for the described area;</li><li>Create and maintain several sales leads sources to support prospecting and sales activity;</li><li>Identify target markets in which to prospect and uncover suitable sales opportunities;</li><li>Develop, optimize, implement and evaluate the TomTom Telematics marketing plan and activities within the area organization;</li><li>Liaise and provide guidance to the Sales Management team in the marketing approach;</li><li>Manage the relationship with our outsourced PR company to deliver relevant content and increase brand awareness;</li><li>Working a minimum two days per week from our office in Centurion.</li></ul><p></p><p><b>What do we expect from you?</b></p><p>There is no set route to become a Marketing Manager B2B at TomTom. But to be successful in this role, this is the kind of profile we have in mind:</p><ul><li>University or graduate degree (preferred: marketing, business management);</li><li>Minimum of 3 years relevant work experience in a B2B channel environment is required;</li><li>Preferred marketing knowledge or experience of areas relating to: service industries, fleet management, logistics, transportation, electronics, telecommunications, hi- &nbsp;technology, vertical software or closely related B2B industries;</li><li>Proven experience in designing, implementing and delivering marketing plans with a focus on new business generation;</li><li>Strategic planning skills and to manage multiple tasks and prioritize;</li><li>Excellent&nbsp;organizational and administrative skills;</li><li>Outstanding communicator;</li><li>Strong computer literacy and competency with Microsoft Office packages;</li><li>Driven and ambitious; real passion for the products and markets;</li><li>Entrepreneurial thinking and team player;</li><li>Result oriented, takes initiative, positive attitude;</li></ul><p></p><p><b>What do we offer? </b></p><p></p><p>An adventure in the cutting-edge field of telematics, digital mapping, traffic and navigation solutions; The chance to work in a fast moving, innovative and international environment, dealing with all kind of different countries and cultures; The opportunity to join a dynamic team where your contribution really makes a difference; Contract with flexible benefits, flexible holiday plan, collective health insurance, and pension scheme.</p><p></p><p><b>Who are we?</b></p><p></p><p>Founded in 1991 and headquartered in Amsterdam, we have 4,100 employees worldwide and sell our products in over 36 countries.</p><p>Our business consists of four customer facing business units: Consumer, Automotive, Licensing and Telematics.</p><p>TomTom Telematics is a Business Unit of TomTom dedicated to fleet management, vehicle telematics and connected car services. WEBFLEET is a Software-as-a-Service solution, used by small to large businesses to improve vehicle performance, save fuel, support drivers and increase overall fleet efficiency. In addition, TomTom Telematics provides services for the insurance, rental and leasing industries, car importers and companies that address businesses as well as consumers.</p><p>TomTom Telematics is one of the world’s leading telematics solution providers with more than 696,000 subscriptions worldwide. The company services drivers in more than 60 countries, giving them the industry’s strongest local support network and widest range of sector-specific third party applications and integrations. More than 46,000 customers benefit every day from the high standards of confidentiality, integrity and availability of our ISO/IEC 27001:2013 certified service, re-audited in November 2016.</p><p>For further information, please visit tomtom.com/telematics</p><p>Follow us on Twitter @TomTomWEBFLEET</p><p></p><p><b>Interested?</b></p><p>&nbsp;For the full story about the vacancy or procedure, please click on <a href=\"http://www.tomtom.com/careers\" target=\"_blank\">www.tomtom.com/careers</a> or for specific questions contact Cecilia Clech.</p><p>&nbsp;Pre-employment screening is part of the selection process.</p>",
