    "id": "Digital-Cartographer_JR0000073",
    "title": "Digital Cartographer",
    "description": "<span><p><span>What if we told you that you can achieve more at TomTom in less time than at any other company?</span></p><p></p><p><span>From coding the next product revolution, to selling it, we always want inspired people to join us. </span></p><p></p><p><span>Find the right vacancy for you? Please click Apply.<span>&nbsp;</span>We look forward getting to know you!</span></p></span><p>Our team achieves more every day. So can you.</p><p>With over 1 billion drivers on the road, traffic congestion is a problem felt all over the world. We're contributing to reduce traffic congestion by opening up our unique real time and historical traffic content to governments and enterprises.</p><p>Today we are only just beginning our journey to reduce traffic congestion. Our mission is difficult and there will be many challenges along the way, but we are committed to playing our role in developing a world where everyone has more freedom to move.</p><p>Learn more at: www.youtube.com/watch?v=6Rc12x-XlYQ&nbsp;and&nbsp;www.tomtom.com/manifesto</p><p><b>Sound interesting?</b></p><p><b>Here’s a little taste of your challenge:</b></p><ul><li>Perform creation, maintenance and enhancement of the TT geographical databases by using/interpreting source material as mentioned in the respective Project Instructions and Descriptions.</li><li>Perform quality work by resolving identified database conflicts (online- QC, INCA/Consistency) and perform rework for deviations found during the quality check.</li><li>Work within a region in Content Operations and primarily working on creation and enhancement of source material by using our standard GIS tools   &nbsp;</li></ul><p></p><p><b>What we expect from you:</b></p><ul><li>College or university degree preferred with a background in spatial management, geography, geodesy, GIS or computer science</li><li>Knowledge of Geographic Data Models and data processing</li><li>0-2 years of related work experience</li><li>Ability to work towards defined project goals (Timing, Quality, Output and cost) within Content Production</li><li>Ability to work on many different project types using a variety of tools, processes and methods</li><li>Good multitasking skills and ability to correctly apply specifications across the multitude of projects</li><li>Highly analytical skills interpreting source material correctly according to the specifications</li><li>Ability to work well under pressure</li><li>Assertive, flexible, well organized &amp; reliable</li><li>Ready to work in any of the&nbsp;two shifts&nbsp;(6am - 2pm/ 2 pm - 10 pm)</li></ul><p><b>What you can expect:</b></p><ul><li>You will never get bored! We move fast like a “start-up” but have the benefits of a billion euro company.</li><li>A company culture that likes to work hard and play hard.&nbsp; We like to have fun. There is no sense coming to a job everyday if you don’t like the people you work with.</li><li>Have an idea? A suggestion? A new way of doing something? The founders are still very present in the company and are very accessible. We all are. There is always room for good ideas. Entreprenurialism is valued.</li><li>Decisive actions. We don’t like to wait. It’s in our DNA to move forward. So it only makes sense that we don’t jam the company with lots of layers. We make things happen. Quickly.</li><li>Let’s not forget about the good stuff: flexible benefits (including multisport card), private medical care, 50% product discount and bonus scheme.</li><li>ŁÓDŹ. A pretty cool city to live and work.</li></ul><p></p><p><b>Want to join us?</b></p><p><b>We would like to meet you!</b></p><p>Please apply via tomtom.com/careers.</p><p>We kindly ask you to complete the form and attachments in English.</p><p>Pre-employment screening of all external candidates is part of the selection process.</p>",
