    "title": "System Engineer",
    "description": "<span><p><span>What if we told you that you can achieve more at TomTom in less time than at any other company?</span></p><p></p><p><span>From coding the next product revolution, to selling it, we always want inspired people to join us. </span></p><p></p><p><span>Find the right vacancy for you? Please click Apply.<span>&nbsp;</span>We look forward getting to know you!</span></p></span><p><b>System </b><b>Engineer (Network Operation Center) – Pune (Linux and App support)</b></p><p></p><p><b><i>'Five years from now we'll be active in areas we haven't yet dreamed of',&nbsp;</i></b></p><p><i>Harold Goddijn, CEO TomTom</i><b>.</b></p><p></p><p><b>Where do you want to be?</b></p><p>OTS (Office and Technology Services) delivers its service across the TomTom Organization. They interact with all departments as supplier of IT services and cooperate in projects where IT knowledge is needed.</p><p></p><p>We are looking for the best and brightest minds to join our team. As a key member of our Network Operation Center team, you will be working as a <b><b>System Engineer</b></b> and having hands on experience in skills like : Linux and Windows Infrastructure, Nagios, VMWare/Cloudstack, RHEL/Cent OS, Apache, Tomcat, Shell Scripting.</p><p><br><b><b>Your main responsibilities will be:</b></b></p><p></p><p>Communicate directly with counterparts in customer organizations (OEM), via ticket systems, emails and remote meetings, in a technically clear and accurate yet courteous tone of voice. Communicate with various teams in TomTom’s internal organization, such as Customer Care, various operational and development teams in different PU’s to drive changes and/or the resolution of customer impacting issues. Maintain and improve our NOC technical support teams. You should be able to troubleshoot distributed products (some parts hosted externally). All OS, Application and Hardware related issues on Linux/Windows environment Work closely with developments teams worldwide. Work as Level 2 support engineer and Provide technical guidance and support to other Engineers as needed. Knowledge on Nagios monitoring system will be a plus. Troubleshoot and resolve Linux/Windows/Network/VMWare/Application related problems at level 2 support worldwide as part of a 24/7 operational team. In an environment with Web Services – like REST API &amp; SOAP UI, giving support and assisting TomTom development and automotive customers.</p><p></p><p><b>What do we expect from you?</b></p><p>To be successful in this role, this is the kind of profile we have in mind:</p><ul><li>Strong analytical, problem solving skills; ability to work effectively under pressure.</li><li>Technical Graduation in Computer Science or equivalent University degree is preferable</li><li>Understand product architecture</li><li>Strong technical communication skills written and spoken</li><li>Taking up end to end ownership of incidents and interacting with B2B customers and engineers to drive to a solution.</li><li>Knowledge of ITIL (Incident, Problem and Change Management) process required.</li><li>Execute &amp; support root cause analysis</li><li>Drive solutions for complex incidents.</li><li>Advanced knowledge of Linux OS</li><li>Knowledge on Web Services – REST API &amp; SOAP UI</li><li>Knowledge of Open Source Software like Nagios and JIRA ticketing system.</li><li>Shell/Perl scripting language knowledge preferred</li><li>Self-propelled professional attitude</li><li>Available to work in rotational shifts (24x7 environment)</li></ul><p><b>What do we offer?</b></p><p>An adventure in the cutting-edge field of digital mapping, traffic and navigation solutions; The chance to work in a fast moving, innovative and international environment, dealing with all kind of different countries and cultures; 30 annual leave days, insurance benefits, annual bonus scheme, free transportation facilities and&nbsp; up to 50% discount on TomTom products; Among others, an online learning platform for your development (1500 courses &amp; 11000 e-books).</p><p></p><p><b>Who are we?</b><br><br>TomTom empowers movement. Every day millions of people around the world depend on TomTom to make smarter decisions. We design and develop innovative products that make it easy for people to keep moving towards their goals.<br><br>Our map-based components include map content, online map-based services, real-time traffic, and navigation software. Our consumer products include PNDs, navigation apps, and GPS sports watches. Our main business products are custom in-dash navigation systems and a fleet management system, which is offered to fleet owners as an online service with integrated in-vehicle cellular devices.<br><br>Our business consists of four customer facing business units: Consumer, Automotive, Licensing and Telematics.<br><br>Founded in 1991 and headquartered in Amsterdam, we have 4,000 employees worldwide and sell our products in over 36 countries.</p><p><b><i>TomTom India Private Limited is one of India’s Best IT &amp; IT- BPM Company to Work for - 2015. It is amongst 50 Best IT &amp; IT-BPM companies to work for in India and amongst the Top 5 among Emerging organizations in IT &amp; IT-BPM.</i></b></p><p><br><b>Interested?</b></p><p></p><p>If you are interested in this opportunity, please reach out to rosy.toms@tomtom.com. We look forward to hearing from you!</p><p>Online assessments and pre-employment verification is part of the selection process.</p>",
