    "id": "Sr-System-Engineer_25369-1",
    "title": "Sr System Engineer",
    "description": "<span><p><span>What if we told you that you can achieve more at TomTom in less time than at any other company?</span></p><p></p><p><span>From coding the next product revolution, to selling it, we always want inspired people to join us. </span></p><p></p><p><span>Find the right vacancy for you? Please click Apply.<span>&nbsp;</span>We look forward getting to know you!</span></p></span><p><b>Senior Systems Engineer – OTS - Infra</b></p><p><u><b>About YOU!</b></u></p><p>Are you looking for the next great international challenge in your career and are you ready to join our world-class team of <b><b>System Engineers</b></b> building out our <b><b>Monitoring Platform for CloudStack, OpenStack, Hadoop and other fancy environments</b></b>? Are you looking for a job where you are fully responsible for building a business and promoting state-of-the-art technology and a world-class brand? Then this might be the perfect opportunity for you!</p><p><u><b>About the Business Unit: OTS - Infra&nbsp; </b></u></p><p>Office and Technology Services (OTS) delivers its service across the TomTom Organization. They interact with all departments as supplier of IT services and cooperate in projects where IT knowledge is needed. The involved infrastructure is spread over multiple data centers across the globe.</p><p><u><b>About the position</b></u></p><p>Working within the Office and Technology Services monitoring group, you will play an important role in designing and building the company's monitoring platform. You will build functionality in order to meet and exceed the requirements and expectations coming from other engineering teams and the business. Your expertise as system engineer will be used to build out a flexible and fault-resilient platform on which new monitoring techniques will be implemented. This is a highly technical role with a strong focus on design and development together with the operational support. This is a hands-on role which requires a strong interest in monitoring and a high level of technical knowledge of multiple operating systems together with an open mind to new technologies and ideas. Due to the nature of the work, you come in contact with all technological layers inside the company, requiring you to have broad technical knowledge and be a fast learner.</p><p></p><p><u><b>Tasks and responsibilities include:</b></u></p><p><b><b>- Be part of a team which develops and operates the data logging and monitoring infrastructure.</b></b></p><p><b><b>- Help other teams with setting up data logging and monitoring of their applications.</b></b></p><p><b><b>- Help other teams with implementing reports and dashboards.</b></b></p><p><b><b>- Give Third line operational support on the monitoring platform.</b></b></p><p><b><b>- Execute hands-on monitoring implementation tasks.</b></b></p><p>- Design and implement solutions based on requirements and user stories.</p><p>- Write documentation, handover knowledge, and train other teams.</p><p>- Being able to work on their own in a structured fashion.</p><p>- Be passionate and be creative while maintaining a high standard.</p><p>- Keep up to date with relevant technological developments.</p><p><u><b>Experience with:</b></u></p><p><b><b>- Large ELK-stacks: Elasticsearch,&nbsp;Logstash, and&nbsp;Kibana.</b></b></p><p><b><b>- Time series databases: statsd, graphite, openTSDB, collectd, or others.</b></b></p><p><b><b>- Visualization of metrics and building status dashboards.</b></b></p><p><b><b>- Nagios-based monitoring systems and extentions like Thruk, Mod_Gearman, LiveStatus.</b></b></p><p><b><b>- Log and event processing systems like Rsyslog, Logstash, RabbitMQ, Elasticsearch.</b></b></p><p><b><b>- Kanban methodology.</b></b></p><p><u><b>About YOU in details</b></u><u>:</u></p><p><b><b>- BE/BSc in computer science or related engineering discipline or equivalent through experience.</b></b></p><p><b><b>- 7+ years of experience as Linux System Engineer, Senior System engineer or equivalent designation. </b></b></p><p><b><b>- 3+ years of experience with Elastic Search and Nagios.</b></b></p><p>- Experience with design and administration of Nagios and familiarity with the Nagios ecosystem.</p><p>- Experience with programming in at least one of the languages like Ruby, Python, Perl or bash.</p><p>- Be able to write monitoring (Nagios) checks.</p><p>- Experience with Puppet or similar automation tools.</p><p>- Knowledge how APIs work.</p><p><b><u><b>Requirements </b></u></b></p><p>• At least 7 years as Sr/System Engineer</p><p>• Hands on experience in handling Linux servers and infrastructure components.</p><p>• Knowledge/understanding of Windows environment too.</p><p>• Knowledge of ITIL</p><p>• Excellent communication skills and cross-cultural adaptability</p><p>• Available for travelling, if required.</p><p><u><b>Our Offer</b></u></p><ul><li>The chance to work in a dynamic team with a world-class brand</li><li>Market rate salary &amp; benefits (depending on experience)</li><li>A challenging, fast moving and innovate work environment</li><li>Additional items like employee discounts, recognition awards, seniority programs, as well as on site specific items like running clubs, yoga, social events, charity initiatives, etc. depending on the site<br>&nbsp;<p><b><u>About TomTom</u></b></p><p></p><p>Founded in 1991, TomTom is the world's leading provider of in-car location and navigation products and services focused on providing all drivers with the world's best navigation experience. Headquartered in Amsterdam, TomTom has over 3,500 employees and sells its products in over 40 countries.</p><p>Our products include portable navigation devices, in-dash infotainment systems, fleet management solutions, maps and real-time services, including the award winning HD Traffic.</p><p>By streamlining and integrating our organization, we have created a lean and agile structure enabling us to stay close to our customers and substantially improving our time to market. TomTom comprises of four business units; Consumer, Automotive, Business Solutions and Licensing.</p><p></p><p><b><u>Interested?</u></b></p><p>If you would like to be part of this winning international team and help us further position ourselves as the authority expert in location and navigation solutions, please click <a href=\"http://www.tomtom.jobs/apply.aspx\" target=\"_blank\"><b>here</b></a>.</p><p></p><p>We kindly ask you to complete the form and attachments in English.</p><p></p><p>Pre-employment screening of all external candidates is part of the process.</p></li></ul>",
