    "id": "TomTom---E-Commerce-Intern---Burlington--MA_25604",
    "title": "TomTom - E-Commerce Intern - Burlington, MA",
    "description": "<span><p><span>What if we told you that you can achieve more at TomTom in less time than at any other company?</span></p><p></p><p><span>From coding the next product revolution, to selling it, we always want inspired people to join us. </span></p><p></p><p><span>Find the right vacancy for you? Please click Apply.<span>&nbsp;</span>We look forward getting to know you!</span></p></span><p><b><i><i>'Five years from now we'll be active in areas we haven't yet dreamed of'</i></i>.</b><br><b>Harold Goddijn, CEO TomTom.</b></p><p></p><p>TomTom empowers movement. As an industry leader, we excel at designing and developing innovative products that make it easy for people to keep moving towards their goals. TomTom has grown from a Dutch based start-up company into a multi-national, global brand. As our original founders remain committed to the business, together with TomTom’s global team of passionate and dedicated employees, we will continue to create new products and achieve our goals.</p><p></p><p><b>Where do you want to be?</b></p><p>Are you a recent college grad looking to get experience in the fields of Sales &amp; Marketing?&nbsp;</p><p>Do you have a strong work ethic and desire to learn and be challenged?&nbsp; TomTom is looking for a dynamic, results driven individual to support our e-commerce efforts within the Consumer Business Unit.&nbsp; This position will be based at our US Headquarters in Burlington, MA. We will consider qualified individuals willing to work between 20-40 hours per week.</p><p></p><p>We are looking for an independent self-starter able to be responsible the following activities:</p><ul><li>Website Merchandising (categorization, copy updates, product images)</li><li>Support with promotional planning and launches, seasonal product adds and site maintenance</li><li><span>Perform inventory checks &amp; adjustments on a weekly basis</span></li><li>Support in various data entry projects</li><li>Assist in the identification / fix broken image issues across the site</li><li>Assist in the preparation of weekly marketing reports</li><li><span>General marketing assistance when necessary</span></li><li>Monitor consumer reviews, Q&amp;A, UGC</li><li>Assist with maintenance and updates to email marketing calendars</li><li>Assist with daily execution of email campaigns including bundling of creative assets and email instructions, delivery to ESP, and creative setup, testing, and deployment</li><li>Verify that all email marketing campaigns adhere to quality assurance processing to ensure accuracy and on-time delivery</li></ul><p></p><p><br><b><b>What do we expect from you?</b></b></p><p>To be successful as an E-Commerce Intern, this is the kind of profile we have in mind:</p><ul><li>1-2 years of sales, e-commerce or marketing experience</li><li>Ability to effectively manage multiple priorities and adapt to change in a fast-paced environment</li><li>Proficiency in Microsoft Office (Excel, Outlook, Word, PowerPoint)</li><li>Proficiency in Excel</li><li>Ability to manage assigned workflow and consistently meet deadlines</li><li>Be a self-starter - Able to manage time and duties across multiple team members</li><li>Strong passion for marketing, and e-commerce</li><li>Strong communication skills and the ability to work cross-functionally</li></ul><p></p><p></p><p><b><b>What do we offer?</b></b></p><p>TomTom offers the opportunity to:</p><ul><li>Work in a fast moving, innovative and international environment where team work and creative ideas are nurtured</li><li>Collaborate with passionate colleagues from different countries around the world</li><li>Represent a global brand and leader in the Consumer Electronics industry</li><li>Gain valuable work experience to catapult your career</li><li>Be part of a fun and dynamic team that impacts the growth of our organization<p></p><p><b>Who are we?</b></p></li></ul><p>TomTom empowers movement. Every day millions of people around the world depend on TomTom to make smarter decisions. We design and develop innovative products that make it easy for people to keep moving towards their goals. Our map-based components include map content, online map-based services, real-time traffic, and navigation software. Our consumer products include PNDs, navigation apps, and GPS sports watches. Our main business products are custom in-dash navigation systems and a fleet management system, which is offered to fleet owners as an online service with integrated in-vehicle cellular devices.</p><p>Our business consists of four customer facing business units: Consumer, Automotive, Licensing and Business Solutions. Founded in 1991 and headquartered in Amsterdam, we have 4,000 employees worldwide and sell our products in over 35 countries. For further information, please visit <a href=\"http://www.tomtom.com/\" target=\"_blank\"><span>www.tomtom.com</span></a>.</p><p></p><p><b><b>Interested?</b></b></p><p>If you would like to be part of this winning team and help TomTom further position ourselves as the authority in location and navigation solutions, please apply at: <a href=\"http://www.tomtom.com/careers\" target=\"_blank\">www.tomtom.com/careers</a>.</p><p>Pre-employment screening is part of the selection process.</p><p><b>EOE/Minorities/Females/Vet/Disabled</b></p><p></p>",
