    "id": "Digital-Cartographer-Customer-Service---San-Jose--CA_JR0000076-2",
    "title": "Digital Cartographer/Customer Service - San Jose, CA",
    "description": "<span><p><span>What if we told you that you can achieve more at TomTom in less time than at any other company?</span></p><p></p><p><span>From coding the next product revolution, to selling it, we always want inspired people to join us. </span></p><p></p><p><span>Find the right vacancy for you? Please click Apply.<span>&nbsp;</span>We look forward getting to know you!</span></p></span><p></p><p></p><p><b><i><i>'Five years from now we'll be active in areas we haven't yet dreamed of'</i></i>.</b><br><b>Harold Goddijn, CEO TomTom.</b></p><p></p><p>TomTom empowers movement. As an industry leader, we excel at designing and developing innovative products that make it easy for people to keep moving towards their goals. TomTom has grown from a Dutch based start-up company into a multi-national, global brand. As our original founders remain committed to the business, together with TomTom’s global team of passionate and dedicated employees, we will continue to create new products and achieve our goals.</p><p></p><p><b>Where do you want to be?</b></p><p>As a Digital Cartographer in Traffic and Travel Information Team you will be responsible for making our Traffic and Travel data the most accurate and up-to-date as possible. This is a great opportunity if you are just starting out in your career and interested in maps and location based services. We offer you a challenging role in an international and innovative organization. You will be part of a culturally diverse team, working in the USA with a team from all over the world.</p><p></p><p>We are looking for an independent self-starter able to own the following activities:</p><ul><li>Responsible for validating information involving traffic incidents, road closures, speed traps, red lights and other relevant traffic and travel information</li><li>Proactively research for new information regarding traffic and travel and update the database</li><li>Use external sources, customer feedback and internal tools to incrementally improve the quality of our traffic and travel information databases</li><li>You will resolve business-to-business and customer care escalations</li><li>You will be an expert in the countries and states which you oversee; proactively searching for new information</li><li>Maintain a high level of knowledge about TomTom’s products and services</li></ul><p></p><p>In addition, the Digital Cartographer’s responsibility will include occasional field testing. This will entail drive testing to ensure optimal end-to-end customer experiences across platforms. After performing the field testing you will report the end user experience for traffic and travel services to help product management and software engineering to further innovate.</p><ul><li>You will perform regular drive test in the USA and primarily in the TomTom office location area to assure end to end customer experience is aligned to the quality of traffic and travel information; by exceptional request you may need to perform drive test in a different state within the USA</li><li>A clean Driver’s License is mandatory</li></ul><p></p><p><b>What we expect from you: </b></p><ul><li><b><span>Bachelor degree </span></b></li><li><b><span>Knowledge or interest in geography, maps, GIS</span></b></li><li><b><span>Experience resolving customer issues</span></b></li><li><b><span>Ability to prioritize, work autonomously and take initiative</span></b></li><li>Fluent in English (company language). Good communication skills both written and spoken. Additional languages are an advantage. Spanish is a plus.</li><li><b><span>Strong attention to detail and quality driven</span></b></li><li><b><span>Willing to share information, coach and train</span></b></li><li><b><span>US Passport or ability to obtain a US Passport for occasional travel to TomTom’s headquarters in Amsterdam</span></b></li></ul><p></p><p><b><b>What do we offer? </b></b></p><ul><li>The chance to work in a fast moving, innovative and international environment where team work and creative ideas are nurtured.</li><li>The opportunity to work with passionate colleagues from different countries.</li><li>Compensation includes a generous base salary, a commission scheme, 15 PTO days, 12 company holidays and 3 additional days to perform community service annually.</li><li>Our benefits package includes medical, dental, vision, disability, life and 401(k).</li></ul><p></p><p><b>Who is TomTom?</b></p><p>TomTom empowers movement. Every day millions of people around the world depend on TomTom to make smarter decisions. We design and develop innovative products that make it easy for people to keep moving towards their goals. Our map-based components include map content, online map-based services, real-time traffic, and navigation software. Our consumer products include PNDs, navigation apps, and GPS sports watches. Our main business products are custom in-dash navigation systems and a fleet management system, which is offered to fleet owners as an online service with integrated in-vehicle cellular devices.</p><p>Our business consists of four customer facing business units: Consumer, Automotive, Licensing and Business Solutions. Founded in 1991 and headquartered in Amsterdam, we have 3,600 employees worldwide and sell our products in over 35 countries. For further information, please visit <a href=\"http://www.tomtom.com/\" target=\"_blank\"><span>www.tomtom.com</span></a>.</p><p></p><p><b><b>Interested?</b></b></p><p>If you would like to be part of this winning international team and help TomTom further position ourselves as the authority in location and navigation solutions, please apply at: <a href=\"http://www.tomtom.com/careers\" target=\"_blank\">www.tomtom.com/careers</a>.</p><p>Pre-employment screening is part of the selection process.</p><p><b>EOE/Minorities/Females/Vet/Disabled</b></p>",
