    "id": "Social-Media-Intern---English-native_JR0000173-1",
    "title": "Social Media Intern - English native",
    "description": "<span><p><span>What if we told you that you can achieve more at TomTom in less time than at any other company?</span></p><p></p><p><span>From coding the next product revolution, to selling it, we always want inspired people to join us. </span></p><p></p><p><span>Find the right vacancy for you? Please click Apply.<span>&nbsp;</span>We look forward getting to know you!</span></p></span><p><b>'Five years from now we'll be active in areas we haven't yet dreamed of'.</b></p><p><i>Harold Goddijn, CEO TomTom.</i></p><p></p><p>TomTom empowers movement. Every day millions of people around the world depend on TomTom to make smarter decisions. Would you like contribute in designing and developing innovative products that make it easy for people to keep moving towards their goals?</p><p></p><p><b>Where do you want to be?</b></p><p>Are you looking for an extreme cool challenge to grow yourself and be rewarded for your enormous effort? Are you looking for an internship where you have a lot of responsibility and promoting state-of-the-art technology and a world-class brand? Then this might be the right opportunity for you! We are looking for the best and brightest minds to join our Social Media team. The experience and future opportunities will include:</p><p></p><ul><li>You’ll be part of the Global Corporate Communications team, actively contributing for creation and activation of social media campaigns to support company-wide activity, working on exciting topics such as Autonomous Driving, Smart Cities, Wearables and Technology Leadership.</li><li>Support the day to day involvement in multiple social media platforms;</li><li>Assist with the development and engagement of online communities;</li><li>Assist in the implementation of social media marketing campaigns and with the analysis of social media metrics and identification of influencers;</li><li>Support the activity of link prospecting;</li><li>Aid in the development of social media reporting standards and identifying key metrics.</li></ul><p><b>What do we expect from you?</b></p><p>To be a successful Social Media Intern, this is the kind of profile we have in mind:</p><ul><li>Bachelor/Master student in Marketing, Communications/PR, Interactive Media, Information Technology, International Business, or a related discipline;</li><li>You are a native English speaker or fluent in English (written and Verbal), with strong communication skills;</li><li>The ability to speak another EU language is an advantage;</li><li>You are a team player with a dynamic, outgoing personality, and an affinity for technology;</li><li>You possess excellent computer skills with an interest in online and social media trends;</li><li>You are familiar with social media platforms and best practices;</li><li>You are passionate about social media, creating content, and cultivating fan engagement and growth;</li><li>You should be enrolled as a student for the complete duration of the internship;</li><li>You should only apply if you are an EU citizen due to working permit regulations.</li></ul><p><b>What do we offer?</b></p><ul><li>An adventure in the cutting-edge field of digital mapping, traffic and navigation solutions;</li><li>The chance to work in a fast moving, innovative and international environment, dealing with all kind of different countries and cultures;</li><li>6-12 months internship contract;</li><li>500 Euros (Gross based on full time work);</li><li>The exciting opportunity to be part of our internship program Interns on Track.</li></ul><p><b>Who are we?</b></p><p></p><p>Our map-based components include map content, online map-based services, real-time traffic, and navigation software. Our consumer products include PNDs, navigation apps, GPS sports watches, and action cameras. Our main business products are custom in-dash navigation systems and a fleet management system, which is offered to fleet owners as an online service with integrated in-vehicle cellular devices.</p><p>Our business consists of four customer facing business units: Consumer, Automotive, Licensing and Telematics.</p><p>Founded in 1991 and headquartered in Amsterdam, we have 4,000 employees worldwide and sell our products in over 36 countries. For further information, please visit www.tomtom.com</p><p>Interested?</p><p>For the full story about the vacancy (ref job ID 23939) or procedure, please click on the apply button, and go to www.tomtom.com/careers</p>",
