    "id": "Research-Engineer-Java-for-Travel-Information-Development_JR0000118-1",
    "title": "Research Engineer Java for Travel Information Development",
    "description": "<span><p><span>What if we told you that you can achieve more at TomTom in less time than at any other company?</span></p><p></p><p><span>From coding the next product revolution, to selling it, we always want inspired people to join us. </span></p><p></p><p><span>Find the right vacancy for you? Please click Apply.<span>&nbsp;</span>We look forward getting to know you!</span></p></span><span><p><b><i>'Five years from now we'll be active in areas we haven't yet dreamed of'</i></b><b>.</b><br><i>Harold Goddijn, CEO TomTom</i><b>.</b></p><p></p><p><b>Where do you want to be?</b></p><p>Do you want to contribute to new and innovative content services improving the driving experience of millions of TomTom users worldwide? Would you like to develop new algorithms &amp; platforms for Big-data-analysis and -fusion from the very first idea to the implementation of production code?</p><p></p><p><b>You and TomTom</b></p><p>We are looking for the best and brightest minds in Algorithms with programming-experience in Java and Python to join our Travel Information Development Team. Together, we will create and extend tools to process, visualize, and statistically analyse rich location-based information streams. During all this you’ll be communicating and documenting about tools, software components, development progress and analysis results to fellow team-members and stakeholders.</p><p></p><p>As a member of the Travel Information Development team, you are asked to deliver the following:</p><p>High-performing algorithms to extract meaningful information from large &amp; imperfect data sets &nbsp;</p><p>Design and implement efficient &amp; scalable environments for offline and real-time data processing</p><p>Collaborate with a top-level international development team</p><p>Contribute to the conceptualization of novel travel-information services and products</p><p></p><p><b>What do we expect from you?</b></p><p>There is no set route to becoming a Research Engineer at TomTom. But this is the kind of profile we have in mind for someone to be successful in this particular role:</p><ul><li>Very good knowledge of Java and/or python (alternatively C++ or any other OO language) and development in a UNIX/Linux environment;</li><li>High proficiency in designing and implementing efficient algorithms &amp; data structures;</li><li>Advantageous: Strong background in data-mining and statistical data analysis;</li><li>Ideally: Experience with location-based content and Geographic-Information-Systems (GIS) tools;</li><li>Good written and oral language skills in English.</li></ul><p><br><b>What do we offer? </b></p></span><p>You will never get bored!&nbsp; We move fast like a “start-up” but have the benefits of a billion euro company. A company culture that likes to work hard and play hard.&nbsp; We like to have fun.&nbsp; There is no sense coming to a job everyday if you don’t like the people you work with. The opportunity to contribute to new products from the very beginnings of research &amp; design up to the implementation in high-quality production code. An adventure in data-mining and -analysis of one of the largest traffic data-streams worldwide. Being part of modern software development in an international working environment where creativity and algorithmic thinking are as highly valued as team-work and open communication.</p><p></p><p><b>Who are we?</b></p><p>TomTom’s department of Traffic and Travel Information is a leading supplier of traffic and travel information. With TomTom Traffic and IQ Routes TomTom created two of the most advanced traffic solutions based on floating car data. In the spirit of these award-winning products our goal is to find new solutions to traffic problems based on real-life data. You will work in an agile development team of creative, motivated young professionals with an open-minded and cooperative attitude.</p><p></p><p></p><p><b>Interested?</b></p><p>Online assessments and pre-employment screening is part of the selection process.</p><p></p><p></p>",
