    "title": "Marketing Analysis Intern",
    "description": "<span><p><span>What if we told you that you can achieve more at TomTom in less time than at any other company?</span></p><p></p><p><span>From coding the next product revolution, to selling it, we always want inspired people to join us. </span></p><p></p><p><span>Find the right vacancy for you? Please click Apply.<span>&nbsp;</span>We look forward getting to know you!</span></p></span><p><b><i>Marketing Analyst Internship</i></b></p><p></p><p><b><i>'Five years from now we'll be active in areas we haven't yet dreamed of'</i></b><b>.</b><br><b>Harold Goddijn, CEO TomTom.</b></p><p>TomTom empowers movement. Every day millions of people around the world depend on TomTom to make smarter decisions. Would you like to contribute in designing and developing innovative products that make it easy for people to keep moving towards their goals?</p><p><b>Where do you want to be?</b></p><p>We are looking for the best and brightest minds in Marketing Analysis to join our Marketing Consumer team within our Marketing Intelligence Unit. This internship is a unique opportunity to learn a combination of analytical skills in digital communication and communication skills while working on improving the customer and journalist perception of our complete global product line-up. You will be reporting to the Global Ratings and Reviews Manager within the Marketing Intelligence Unit and working closely with multiple international Marketing and Product Development stakeholders within the company. Ratings and Reviews are relevant to all of these stakeholders, and aligning the approach and strategy between them is essential to bringing our products to even higher popularity among customers.</p><p>As a member of the Global Marketing&nbsp;team, you will have to deliver the following:</p><ul><li>Gather, analyse and understand data to report on customer reviews from e-tail websites (e.g. Amazon) to help both Marketing and Product Development obtain valuable product insight that helps drive their decision making in terms of product presentation/improvements;</li><li>Together with the team, create and run initiatives based on the insights you find in order to make sure customers are interested in and understand our products thus raising the quantity and quality of product reviews.</li><li>Monitor engagement in product reviews in multiple countries and from many sources (blogs, press, e-tailers, etc.) and coordinate a team of TomTom agents who handle responses in several languages;</li><li>Help develop reviews and ratings tactics/best practice guidelines for both that can then be implemented by the Marketing teams in local markets.</li></ul><p><b>What do we expect from you?</b></p><p>To be a successful Marketing Analysis intern, this is the kind of profile we have in mind:</p><ul><li>Bachelor/Master student in the field of (Technical) Business Administration, Marketing or IT/Computer Science, with a focus on Project management and analytics</li><li>You have strong analytical skills and excellent organizational skills; experience in using Excel</li><li>You possess strong writing and communication skills in English (native/near-native), as well as another EU language (German is strongly preferred);</li><li>You have a sense of responsibility and attention to detail (your work will be analyzed and looked at daily as many stakeholders benefit from it);</li><li><b>You should be&nbsp;enrolled as fulltime student for the complete duration of the internship;</b></li><li>You should only apply if you are an EU citizen due to working permit regulations.</li></ul><p><b>What do we offer?</b></p><ul><li>An adventure in the cutting-edge field of digital mapping, traffic and navigation solutions;</li><li>The opportunity to work in a fast moving, innovative and international environment, dealing with all kind of different countries and cultures;</li><li>500 Euros (Gross based on full time work);</li><li>A 6-12 months internship contract;</li><li>The exciting opportunity to be part of our internship program Interns on Track.</li></ul><p><b>Who are we?</b></p><p>Our map-based components include map content, online map-based services, real-time traffic, and navigation software. Our consumer products include PNDs, navigation apps, and GPS sports watches. Our main business products are custom in-dash navigation systems and a fleet management system, which is offered to fleet owners as an online service with integrated in-vehicle cellular devices.</p><p>Our business consists of four customer facing business units: Consumer, Automotive, Licensing and Telematics.</p><p>Founded in 1991 and headquartered in Amsterdam, we have 4,000 employees worldwide and sell our products in over 36 countries. For further information, please visit&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.tomtom.com/\" target=\"_blank\">www.tomtom.com</a></p><p><b>Interested?</b></p><p>For the full story about the vacancy (ref <b>job ID</b>) or procedure, please click on the apply button, and go to&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.tomtom.jobs/\" target=\"_blank\">www.tomtom.jobs</a></p><p></p>",
