    "title": "IT Service Level Reporting intern",
    "description": "<span><p><span>What if we told you that you can achieve more at TomTom in less time than at any other company?</span></p><p></p><p><span>From coding the next product revolution, to selling it, we always want inspired people to join us. </span></p><p></p><p><span>Find the right vacancy for you? Please click Apply.<span>&nbsp;</span>We look forward getting to know you!</span></p></span><p><b>IT Service Level Reporting intern</b></p><p><b><i>'Five years from now we'll be active in areas we haven't yet dreamed of'</i></b><b>.</b><br><b>Harold Goddijn, CEO TomTom.</b></p><p></p><p>TomTom empowers movement. Every day millions of people around the world depend on TomTom to make smarter decisions. The project has as goal to create a process to provide fully automated reports to our internal and external customers. These monthly reports show our service levels, such as availability, for TomTom services such as real-time traffic going to navigation devices. You would be introducing your TomTom colleagues to a more efficient process&nbsp; and providing a way to better communicate to our customers, especially important for our Automotive customers.</p><p></p><p><b>Where do you want to be?</b></p><p>We are looking for the best and brightest minds to improve our service reports and reporting process.&nbsp;The experience will include being part of a complex application development and operations organization, learning what it takes to provide real-time services to customers with high reliability.&nbsp; You will liaise with service level managers to understand what the details of what needs to be provided in the reports.&nbsp; You will work with international teams to understand the monitoring and the data, identifying issues with the data and monitoring systems, as well as with the process.&nbsp; You will investigate together with automation engineers how to best gather the data and automate the reports. You will have the chance for hands-on technical implementaion as well as process implementation.</p><p>As a member of the global Business Process Solution team, you will have to deliver the following:</p><p>Take over the current report creation process and keep it running while working on the improvements. Assess the current process, determine the points for improvement and the best solutions. Implement the solution together with others where needed.&nbsp; Implementation may be process-oriented as well as technical. Document and roll out the new process to the service level managers.</p><p></p><p><b>What do we expect from you?</b></p><p></p><p>To be successful in as a Data migration intern, this is the kind of profile we have in mind:</p><ul><li>Bachelor/Master student in the field of IT/Computer Science</li><li>You have excellent MS office skills (Word, Excel, Powerpoint)</li><li>Interest in both the technical and business side of IT.</li><li>You have a basic understanding of Project Management</li><li>You have good communication skills in both written and spoken English</li><li>You are eager to learn and do at the same time</li><li>You pride yourself with great accuracy and reliability</li><li><b>You should be </b><b>enrolled as fulltime student for the complete duration of the internship</b></li><li>You should only apply if you are an EU citizen due to working permit regulations</li></ul><p></p><p><b>What do we offer? </b></p><p></p><p>An adventure in the cutting-edge field of digital mapping, traffic and navigation solutions;</p><p>The opportunity to work in a fast moving, innovative and international environment, dealing with all kind of different countries and cultures;</p><p>500 Euros (Gross based on full time work);</p><p>A 4 months internship contract</p><p></p><p>The exciting opportunity to be part of our internship program Interns on Track.</p><p></p><p><b>Who are we?</b></p><p></p><p>Our map-based components include map content, online map-based services, real-time traffic, and navigation software. Our consumer products include PNDs, navigation apps, GPS sports watches, and action cameras. Our main business products are custom in-dash navigation systems and a fleet management system, which is offered to fleet owners as an online service with integrated in-vehicle cellular devices.</p><p></p><p>Our business consists of four customer facing business units: Consumer, Automotive, Licensing and Telematics.</p><p></p><p>Founded in 1991 and headquartered in Amsterdam, we have 4,000 employees worldwide and sell our products in over 36 countries. For further information, please visit&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.tomtom.com/\" target=\"_blank\">www.tomtom.com</a></p><p></p><p><b>Interested?</b></p><p></p><p>For the full story about the vacancy or procedure, please click on the apply button, and go to&nbsp; <a href=\"http://www.tomtom.jobs\" target=\"_blank\">www.tomtom.c</a>om/careers</p><p></p><p></p>",
