    "id": "Software-Engineer-C---on-Automotive-platforms----QNX--AOSP--WinCE-OR-LINUX-_JR0000250-1",
    "title": "Software Engineer C++ on Automotive platforms ( (QNX, AOSP, WinCE OR LINUX)",
    "description": "<span><p><span>What if we told you that you can achieve more at TomTom in less time than at any other company?</span></p><p></p><p><span>From coding the next product revolution, to selling it, we always want inspired people to join us. </span></p><p></p><p><span>Find the right vacancy for you? Please click Apply.<span>&nbsp;</span>We look forward getting to know you!</span></p></span><p>Our team <b>achieves more</b> every day. So can you.</p><p></p><p>We have been making built-in car navigation since 2008, introduced the connected car in 2010 and are a major player in the area of Highly Automated Driving. And, we are not slowing down. More info about TomTom Automotive can be found <a href=\"http://automotive.tomtom.com/en/connected-navigation-system?_ga=1.133545546.533444928.1452166059\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>.</p><ul><li>Would you like to develop connected navigation products for the car industry that contribute to the FUTURE OF DRIVING?</li><li>Do you want to play a key role in bringing the latest innovation to automotive end users?&nbsp;</li><li>Do you want to be part of an Agile and international working environment, allowing you to develop yourself?</li><li>What about being a part of a company pushing the envelope in HIGHLY AUTOMATED DRIVING</li></ul><p></p><p></p><p><b>Sound interesting?</b></p><p>We are looking for the brightest C++ developers to join our Automotive team in Eindhoven. Your team is responsible creating &nbsp;TomTom’s next-generation connected navigation products.</p><p></p><p></p><p><b>Here’s a little taste of your challenge</b></p><ul><li>Propose innovative solutions to technical issues and communicate with the team to collaborate accordingly.</li><li>Realize innovative in-car navigation solutions using C++ or Java.</li><li>Port the in-car navigation suite to different automotive platforms: QNX, Linux, AOSP etc..</li><li>Work according to Agile methodology (Scrum, SAFe) including performing code reviews, design reviews, testing and writing documentation.</li></ul><p></p><p></p><p><b>What we expect from you</b></p><ul><li>Extensive knowledge of and experience with C++, knowledge of Java, Python, and/or OO practices is an advantage.</li><li>Knowledgeable about Operating System concepts and cross-platform development.</li><li>Professional experience in using unit test frameworks.</li><li>Hands-on mind-set and strong co-operative skills (communicate, listen, understand, convince, discuss, team building).</li><li>Positive-critical mind-set regarding product quality.</li><li>Analytical skills to determine and improve the testability of development deliverables and to find root causes and solutions for detected issues.</li></ul><p></p><p></p><p><b>What you can expect from us</b></p><ul><li>You will never get bored!&nbsp; We move fast like a “start-up” but have the benefits of a billion euro company.</li><li>An adventure in the cutting-edge field of digital mapping, traffic and navigation solutions.</li><li>A company culture that likes to work hard and play hard.&nbsp; We like to have fun.&nbsp; There is no sense coming to a job everyday if you don’t like the people you work with.</li><li>The opportunity to keep on developing hands-on after the Senior stage; become the expert and principal developer.</li><li>Decisive actions.&nbsp; We don’t like to wait.&nbsp; It’s in our DNA to move forward.&nbsp; So it only makes sense that we don’t jam the company with lots of layers.&nbsp; We make things happen.&nbsp; Quickly.</li><li>Indefinite contract, flexible benefits, 25 annual leave days, flexible holiday plan, collective health insurance, pension scheme, up to 50% discount on products, bonus scheme and International relocation package (if applicable).</li><li>Eindhoven.&nbsp; A pretty cool city to live and work. Many international people working in this silicon valley of Europe!</li></ul><p></p><p></p><p><b>Want to join us and be part of the FUTURE OF DRIVING?</b></p><p><i>We would like to meet you!</i></p><p>We kindly ask you to complete the form and attachments in English.</p><p>Pre-employment screening of all external candidates is part of the selection process.</p>",
