    "title": "Product Owner Support Intern",
    "description": "<span><p><span>What if we told you that you can achieve more at TomTom in less time than at any other company?</span></p><p></p><p><span>From coding the next product revolution, to selling it, we always want inspired people to join us. </span></p><p></p><p><span>Find the right vacancy for you? Please click Apply.<span>&nbsp;</span>We look forward getting to know you!</span></p></span><p><b><i>'Five years from now we'll be active in areas we haven't yet dreamed of'</i></b><b>.</b><br><b>Harold Goddijn, CEO TomTom.</b></p><p></p><p>TomTom empowers movement. Every day millions of people around the world depend on TomTom to make smarter decisions. Would you like to contribute in designing and developing innovative products that make it easy for people to keep moving towards their goals?</p><p></p><p><b>Where do you want to be?</b></p><p>We are looking for the best and brightest minds to join our System integration Test team.</p><p>As a member of the global System Integration team, you will have to deliver the following:</p><p></p><ul><li>Work with Product Owner to document the business requirements in the form of user stories and keep backlog up to date</li><li>Understand the System Integration Test ecosystem and document the user stories with appropriate information</li><li>Look at software from a usability and testability point of view, without having a testing-only mindset</li><li><b>Cooperate closely &nbsp;with internal clients and stakeholders</b></li></ul><p></p><p><b>What do we expect from you?</b></p><p></p><p>To be successful in as a Product Owner support intern, this is the kind of profile we have in mind:</p><p></p><ul><li>Pursuing University degree related to Business/Requirement Management of Technical System</li><li>Profound knowledge of Agile frameworks (Scaled Agile is a plus)</li><li>You know and understand the Devops culture</li><li>You know about continuous delivery/continuous integration process</li><li>Excited about automated deployment and testing techniques and tools</li><li><b>Never-ending curiosity; technologies, paradigms, new research domains intrigue you beyond measure</b></li><li><b>Agile thinker and team player</b></li><li><b>Excellent English language skills (written and oral);</b></li><li><b>Pro-active, motivated, independent and performance driven;</b></li><li><b>Excited about making processes more efficient;&nbsp; </b></li><li><b>You should be </b><b>enrolled as fulltime student for the complete duration of the internship;</b></li><li>You should only apply if you are an EU citizen due to working permit regulations.</li></ul><p></p><p><b>What do we offer? </b></p><p></p><p>An adventure in the cutting-edge field of digital mapping, traffic and navigation solutions; The opportunity to work in a fast moving, innovative and international environment, dealing with all kind of different countries and cultures; 500 Euros (Gross based on full time work); A 6 months internship contract The exciting opportunity to be part of our internship program Interns on Track.</p><p></p><p><b>Who are we?</b></p><p></p><p>Our map-based components include map content, online map-based services, real-time traffic, and navigation software. Our consumer products include PNDs, navigation apps, GPS sports watches, and action cameras. Our main business products are custom in-dash navigation systems and a fleet management system, which is offered to fleet owners as an online service with integrated in-vehicle cellular devices.</p><p></p><p>Our business consists of four customer facing business units: Consumer, Automotive, Licensing and Telematics.</p><p></p><p>Founded in 1991 and headquartered in Amsterdam, we have 4,000 employees worldwide and sell our products in over 36 countries. For further information, please visit&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.tomtom.com/\" target=\"_blank\">www.tomtom.com</a></p><p></p><p></p><p><b>Interested?</b></p><p></p><p>For the full story about the vacancy (24613) or procedure, please click on the apply button, and go to&nbsp; <a href=\"http://www.tomtom.com/careers\" target=\"_blank\">www.tomtom.com/careers</a></p>",
