    "id": "Customer-Support-Representative-B2B---English-and-Dutch-speaker_JR0000241",
    "title": "Customer Support Representative B2B - English and Dutch speaker",
    "description": "<p><b>Where do you want to be?</b></p><p></p><p>We are looking for the best and brightest minds to join our Customer Support team within our <b>Telematics Business Unit</b>. &nbsp;Our team supports B2B resellers and customers from different countries. In addition, team members are working on additional projects or specializing on certain topics.</p><p>The experience and future opportunities will include<b>:</b></p><ul><li>Provide product information and effective technical support through multiple channels (phone, e-mail, chat);</li><li>Investigate and take care of large and complex technical support matters, where necessary working closely together with peers across all departments to ensure an exceptional and seamless experience for our customers;</li><li>Contribute to additional support programs/projects (e.g content delivery, product expertise, targeted proactive support activities.</li></ul><p></p><p>As a member of the global Customer Support team, you are asked to deliver the following:</p><ul><li>An effective technical support (unburdening the customer wherever possible, thinking ahead to cover expected follow-up topics and an exceptional and seamless experience);</li><li>Provide with first-class, high-quality, professional responses to customer enquiries within agreed performance levels;</li><li>A constant and pro-active improvement of product/support knowledge;</li><li>Pro-active engagement in additional activities (when the regular workload allows it).</li></ul><p></p><p><b>What do we expect from you?</b></p><p></p><p>There is no set route to become <b>Customer Support Representative B2B</b>, but to be successful in this role this is the kind of profile we have in mind:</p><ul><li>Business proficiency in <b>Dutch </b>and<b> English </b>is required. Good language skills in Danish or other languages are advantageous;</li><li>Excellent proven technical customer support experience of at least 2 years in an international B2B environment;</li><li>Excellent communication skills (both written and verbal) as well as a talent to develop good relationships with business customers;</li><li>You are flexible and team player with time management skills;</li><li>Technically proficient;&nbsp;knowledge on fields relevant to Telematics (vehicle electronics, telecommunication, GPS) is a clear advantage; basic knowledge of PC hardware; good knowledge of Windows OS; knowledge of web browsers (Internet Explorer, Mozilla).<p></p></li></ul><p><b>What do we offer?</b></p><p></p><ul><li>A very exciting role in the cutting-edge field of Telematics (more than 30% of annual growth);</li><li>Intensive on-the-job-training (regular travels to Eindhoven required)</li><li>The chance to work in a fast moving, innovative and international environment, dealing with all kind of different countries and cultures;</li><li>Contract with flexible benefits, flexible holiday plan, collective health insurance, pension scheme, up to 50% discount on products, bonus scheme.</li></ul><p></p><p><b>Who are we?</b></p><p></p><p><span>Founded in 1991 and headquartered in Amsterdam, we have 4,100 employees worldwide and sell our products in over 36 countries. </span></p><p><span>Our business consists of four customer facing business units: Consumer, Automotive, Licensing and Telematics.</span></p><p><span>TomTom Telematics is the fastest growing Business Unit of TomTom, and one of the world’s leading providers of fleet management solutions and professional telematics services, delivered as “Software-as-a-Service (SaaS)”. Our products are designed to help professional drivers to drive greener, safer and more efficiently. Our award winning online platform, WEBFLEET, is highly scalable and has the highest standards in terms of reliability and security. TomTom Telematics services more than 50,000 fleet customers in 60 countries with more than 650,000 active monitored units/vehicles and is Europe’s largest and fastest growing fleet management service provider.</span></p><p><span>For further information, please visit www.tomtom.com</span></p><p></p><p><b>Interested?</b></p><p>If you would like to be part of this winning team and help us further position ourselves as the authority in location and navigation solutions, please click on the apply button or go to&nbsp; www.tomtom.com/careers</p><p></p><p>Pre-employment screening is part of the selection process.&nbsp;</p>",
