    "title": "Embedded Software Engineer C",
    "description": "<p>&nbsp;Our team<span>&nbsp;</span><b>achieves more</b><span>&nbsp;</span>every day. So can you.</p><p>&nbsp;We have been making sports devices since 2011 and have been innovating ever since.</p><p>And, we are not slowing down. &nbsp;</p><ul><li>Do you want to work on systems involving embedded, mobile, web front end, server side?</li><li>Do you refer to yourself as the Master of Embedded Software Engineering (C)?</li><li>Do you want to work on the next generation of wearable technologies? Who doesn’t actually?</li><li>What about making a difference with your OWN ideas for features and improvements, getting a top place on the backlog?</li></ul><p></p><p><b>Sound interesting?</b></p><p>How about -<span>&nbsp;</span><b>Want to code the future?</b></p><p>Pretty big thinking. We like to think we make that happen.</p><p>We’re looking for software engineers to join us. Within the team, you'll be developing features in a test system used by millions of sports devices across the globe</p><p></p><p><b>Here’s a little taste of your challenge</b></p><ul><li>Development of embedded software for consumer electronics products</li><li>Software design up to and including input in to the architectural design.</li><li>Support for the Electronic Engineering teams as required</li><li>Providing support to Production Engineering and manufacturing to aid the efficient manufacture of our products</li><li>RTOS (real-time OS) development and software architecture.</li><li>Device driver development.</li></ul><p></p><p><b>What we expect from you</b></p><ul><li>University/College level, experienced professional</li><li>Excellent knowledge of C&nbsp;in embedded and mobile environments</li><li>C++ experience would also be advantageous.</li><li>Knowledge of GPS technologies and relevant open source technology</li><li>Strong analytical skills&nbsp;</li><li>Excellent English communications skills&nbsp;</li><li>Proven experience in delivering successfully within a scaled Agile framework</li><li>Battery powered device development.</li><li>Familiarity with test-driven development methodologies.&nbsp;&nbsp;</li><li>Knowledge of embedded systems security mechanisms</li></ul><p></p><p><b>What you can expect from us</b></p><ul><li>You will never get bored!&nbsp; We move fast like a “start-up” but have the benefits of a billion euro company.</li><li>A company culture that likes to work hard and play hard.&nbsp; We like to have fun.&nbsp; There is no sense coming to a job everyday if you don’t like the people you work with.</li><li>Have an idea? A suggestion? A new way of doing something?&nbsp; The founders are still very present in the company and are very accessible.&nbsp; We all are.&nbsp; There is always room for good ideas.&nbsp; Entrepreneurialism is valued.</li><li>Decisive actions.&nbsp; We don’t like to wait.&nbsp; It’s in our DNA to move forward.&nbsp; So it only makes sense that we don’t jam the company with lots of layers.&nbsp; We make things happen.&nbsp; Quickly.</li></ul><p></p><p><b>Want to join us?</b></p><p><i>We would like to meet you!</i></p><p>We kindly ask you to complete the form and attachments in English.</p><p>Pre-employment screening of all external candidates is part of the selection process.</p>",
