    "id": "Category-Manager-2-wheel---Large-Vehicles---London---Paris_JR0000180-3",
    "title": "Category Manager 2-wheel & Large Vehicles - London / Paris",
    "description": "<p><b><i>'Five years from now we'll be active in areas we haven't yet dreamed of'</i></b><b>.</b><br><b>Harold Goddijn, CEO TomTom.</b></p><p>TomTom empowers movement. Every day millions of people around the world depend on TomTom to make smarter decisions. Would you like contribute in designing and developing innovative products that make it easy for people to keep moving towards their goals?</p><p></p><p><b>Where do you want to be?</b></p><p>We are looking for the best and brightest entrepreneurial minds in Sales to join our consumer team in EMEA HQ.</p><p></p><p>In this role, your main responsibility is being responsible for the sales development and management of all products to the 2-wheel &amp; Large Vehicles channels in UK &amp; France.</p><p>You will have to build long term relationship with those channels, key partners and category driver for the local retail and online sales teams.</p><p>The role also includes presenting business plans, leading on various projects, look continuously for new opportunities and frequent meetings with distributors, resellers and B2B customers</p><p></p><p>As a member of the EMEA Consumer Sales team, you will have to deliver the following:</p><ul><li>Be responsible for the category results and executing GoToMarket plans in the selected markets</li><li>Achieve quarterly Revenue &amp; Profit for the total product category</li><li>Provide monthly a 6-months rolling product category forecast in volume and value by channel/ account.</li><li>Develop and agree annual plans for all channels &nbsp;(Specialists, Retail, Online) , strategic partners and review quarterly</li><li>Develop the specialist channel for the product categories and work with the local teams for Retail &amp; Online channels</li><li>Visit key stores, key partners and distributors on a regular basis</li><li>Own, manage in an efficient way the Financial relationships within key partners promotional/ marketing budgets, invoicing and claims management</li><li>Participate actively to the weekly sales and marketing meetings (preparation and minutes of the meetings)</li><li>Submits all written reports, as specified, by the advised deadlines</li><li>Look continuously for new business opportunities</li><li>Feedback the competition’s actions and promotions and follow market trends</li></ul><p></p><p><b>What do we expect from you?</b></p><p>To be successful as a Category Manager, this is the kind of profile we have in mind:</p><ul><li>At least 5 years of international sales experience within specialist/ retail/ online/ B2B in electronics, IT, photo, telecom, connected devices manufacturers</li><li>University degree in sales</li><li>Successful track record in building &amp; managing a multichannel business in different Countries</li><li>Result orientated, resilient, team player, flexible, entrepreneurial and open personality.</li><li>Excellent organizational and business planning skills</li><li>Experience with driving trade marketing activities on the sales floor</li><li>Leadership and coaching abilities for working with Field Account Managers;</li><li>Good level of English and French, both written &amp; spoken.</li><li>Creative and able to analyses market needs, potential trends and formulate appropriate plans and programs.</li><li>Passionate for the job &amp; technology;</li><li>Affinity with the 2 wheel &amp; truck market</li><li>Good combination of analytical and creative capabilities.</li><li>Flexible to work on different organizational levels.</li></ul><p></p><p><b>What do we offer? </b></p><ul><li>An adventure in the cutting-edge field of digital mapping, traffic and navigation solutions;</li><li>Our leadership in the Personal Navigation Devices market</li><li>A highly recognised ,recommended and respected brand</li><li>The chance to work in a fast moving, innovative and international environment, dealing with all kind of different countries and cultures;</li><li>Indefinite contract, flexible benefits, collective health insurance, pension scheme, up to 50% discount on products, bonus scheme;</li><li>The chance to work in a fast moving, innovative and international environment, dealing with all kind of different countries and cultures.</li><li>Be part of the success within the business unit Consumer witch is focused on creating innovative products that provide easy access to the information consumers need to make smarter decisions.</li><li>You will never get bored!&nbsp; We move fast like a “start-up” but have the benefits of a billion-euro company.</li><li>A company culture that likes to work hard and play hard.&nbsp; We like to have fun.&nbsp; There is no sense coming to a job everyday if you don’t like the people you work with.</li><li>Have an idea? A suggestion? A new way of doing something?&nbsp; There is always room for good ideas.&nbsp; Entrepreneurialism is valued.</li><li>The chance to work in a fast moving, innovative and international environment, dealing with all kind of different countries and cultures;</li><li>An adventure in the leading field in our expanding &amp; fast growing Sport business;</li><li>The chance to work for a highly recognised, recommended and respected brand;</li><li>Be part of the success within the business unit Consumer witch is focused on creating innovative products that provide easy access to the information consumers need to make smarter decisions;</li><li>TomTom has&nbsp;plenty of opportunities for personal growth and career development in the coming years;</li><li>Be part of a company who’s in the stage of “back to growth”;</li><li>Market rate salary &amp; benefits (depending on experience).</li></ul><p></p>",
