    "title": "Digital Cartographer - Navigate into the future",
    "description": "<p><b>Where do you want to be?</b></p><p><i>We are looking for the best and brightest minds to join our <b>MAPS Content Operation</b> team. </i></p><p><i>As a member of the <b>Content Operations Data Production Unit</b>, <b>Pune</b> you are expected to deliver the following:</i></p><p><b><i>As a Digital Cartographer, you will be responsible to create and update high quality map database. </i></b> <i>You gain extensive understanding of the TOMTOM specification, processes and editing environment. </i> <i>You build competency in handling multiple map sources while standardizing your base maps.</i> <i>You continuously improve knowledge, skills and expertise in map specifications, editing methodology and processes.&nbsp; </i> <i>You can continuously improve the production target achieving high level of efficiency and quality. </i> <i>You’re proactive, a great team player and above all you love your work.</i></p><p></p><p><b>What do we expect from you?</b></p><p><i>To be successful in this role, this is the kind of profile we have in mind: (Roles &amp; Responsibilities)</i></p><ul><li>Perform TomTom map database updates (create, maintain and enhance) using standard editing tools;</li><li>Interpreting source material base data like imagery, Mobile Mapping video sessions, photographs,&nbsp; raster maps, field survey reports, vector maps, field survey inputs and other GIS sources&nbsp; to perform manual edits in line with the TomTom specification, project specification.</li><li>Understanding and adhering to TomTom specification, Quality reference and processes, Project instruction, and Work instruction.</li><li>Work with little supervisory guidance after the initial theoretical and practical on job training.</li><li>Adherence to Production Targets</li><li>Regular reporting of production hours&nbsp; through defined system</li><li>Improving the content of the TomTom Maps by avoiding quality problems, database integrity, and consistency conflicts and delivering First Time Right.</li><li>Perform corrective actions where ever deviation is observed against quality reference or database integrity.</li><li>Continuously improving knowledge, skills and expertise on TomTom map database specification, editing tools, methods and new country geographies.</li></ul><p><b>What do we offer?</b></p><ul><li>An excitement to work in the cutting-edge geo-field of digital mapping, traffic and navigation solutions</li><li>The chance to work in a fast moving, innovative and international environment, dealing with all kind of different countries and cultures.</li></ul><p></p>",
