    "id": "Resident-Engineer-Gothenburg_JR0000244-1",
    "title": "Resident Engineer Gothenburg",
    "description": "<p>Our team&nbsp;<b>achieves more</b>&nbsp;every day. So can you.<br><br>We have been making built-in car navigation since 2008, introduced the connected car in 2010 and are a major player in the area of Highly Automated Driving. And, we are not slowing down.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><ul><li>Would you like to develop connected navigation products for the car industry that contribute to the FUTURE OF DRIVING?</li><li>Do you want to play a key role in bringing the latest innovation to automotive end users?&nbsp;</li><li>Do you want to be part of an Agile (Scrum, SAFe) and international working environment, allowing you to develop yourself?</li><li>What about being a part of a company pushing the envelope in HIGHLY AUTOMATED DRIVING</li></ul><p><br><b>Sound interesting?</b><br>We are looking for an experienced resident engineer with a strong technical background, experience in complex software projects, and understanding of software development methodologies. You are a natural networker and influencer. You will create a solid relationship between customer and TomTom’s internal teams assuring the customers’ wishes and requests are achieved, while bringing the best of TomTom automotive’s technologies and products. You will operate as a resident engineer with our automotive customers and form the link between them and the development teams operating from the Netherlands and Taiwan.</p><p><br><b>Your core responsibilities are</b></p><ul><li>You are the first point of contact for the customer on product, planning and technical topics including recurring issue tracking</li><li>Attend all relevant project meetings at the customer’s location</li><li>Support integration and validation expeditions together with the customer and ensure thorough follow up</li><li>Working closely together with customer to integrate TomTom assets on customer platforms for demonstrations and research programs</li><li>Establishing technical leadership with support and presentations at customer</li><li>Staying current with the innovations in the domain of connected vehicles, connected navigation, and the asset developments in the various TomTom product units.</li><li>Supporting customer with Quality issues.</li></ul><p><b>What we expect from you</b></p><ul><li>Master's or Bachelor's degree in Computer engineering or equivalent with 3- 5&nbsp;years of experience</li><li>Experience with being a customer interface, preferably&nbsp;in Automotive</li><li>Thorough understanding of navigation, map production, cloud and wireless communication</li><li>Knowledge of Requirements Management and Bug Tracking systems</li><li>Commitment to deliver high quality products</li><li>Leadership skill with ability to influence others across complex organizations</li><li>Ability to work independently as well as part of a team. Self-managing</li><li>Excellent written and oral communication skills in Swedish preferred&nbsp;and English&nbsp;language is a must</li><li>Live in the Gothenburg area or willing to relocate</li><li>Flexibility to travel on occasional basis (20%)</li></ul><p><b>What you can expect from us</b></p><ul><li>You will never get bored!&nbsp; We move fast like a “start-up” but have the benefits of a billion euro company</li><li>An adventure in the cutting-edge field of digital mapping, traffic and navigation solutions</li><li>Decisive actions.&nbsp;We don’t like to wait.&nbsp;It’s in our DNA to move forward.&nbsp;So it only makes sense that we don’t jam the company with lots of layers.&nbsp;We make things happen.&nbsp;Quickly.</li></ul><p><br><b>Want to join us and be part of the FUTURE OF DRIVING?</b><br><i>We would like to meet you!</i><br>Please apply through&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.tomtom.com/careers\" target=\"_blank\">www.tomtom.com/careers</a>. Your recruiter for this vacancy is Timon Krommendam.<br><br>We kindly ask you to complete the form and attachments in English.<br>Pre-employment screening of all external candidates is part of the selection process</p><p></p>",
