    "id": "Customer-Base-Marketeer_JR0000275",
    "title": "Customer Base Marketeer",
    "description": "<p><b><b>Where do you want to be… </b></b>in a year, in 5 years?</p><p></p><p>What if you had the opportunity to achieve more in less time then you could ever imagine?</p><p></p><p>At TomTom, you can.&nbsp;</p><p></p><p>We are looking for a self-starting, data-driven, enthusiastic and experienced Customer Base Marketeer to drive customer base marketing programs for <b><b>TomTom Telematics</b></b>.</p><p><b><b>The&nbsp;Customer Base Marketeer</b></b>&nbsp;will be joining the customer base marketing team, with the overall goal of creating more happy customers, lowering churn and increasing revenue from customers. This is an incredibly exciting opportunity to join us in a state of rapid growth.</p><p></p><p>Sound good so far?</p><p></p><p><b><b>Here’s a little taste of your challenge:</b></b></p><ul><li>Create, implement and execute customer base plans covering activities to cross and upsell for our core countries in Europe;</li><li>Target group segmentation to approach each segment at the right time, in the right channel and with the right message;</li><li>Create email marketing campaigns;</li><li>Analyze and optimize customer journeys and campaigns on an ongoing basis, based on data from CRM (SalesForce) and Eloqua;</li><li>Report on customer base marketing performance.</li></ul><p></p><p><b><b>As a member of the&nbsp;Customer Base Marketing team, you are asked to:</b></b></p><ul><li>Understand and drive upsell and retention programs including the use of email marketing and remarketing strategies;</li><li>Collaborate with regional marketing, telemarketing and sales organization to deliver upsell results;</li><li>Share best practices with sales, other marketing departments and customer support teams;&nbsp;</li><li>Develop a deep understanding of customer personas and their online and offline behavior.</li></ul><p></p><p><b>What we are looking for:</b></p><ul><li>A minimum of 5 years’ experience in managing customer base marketing programs in a fast paced international organization;</li><li>A data driven mindset – be able to work with figures and systems;</li><li>Experience with e-mail marketing, CRM and marketing automation (Eloqua is a plus);</li><li>Strong independent contributor, that excels in a team;</li><li>Be able setup creative campaigns;</li><li>Ability to prioritize and manage multiple projects in a deadline-driven, results-focused environment, while having strong attention to detail;</li><li>Commercial, result driven, self-starter;</li><li>Excellent English oral and written communication skills.</li></ul><p></p><p><b>What you can expect:</b></p><ul><li>An adventure in the cutting-edge SaaS solutions and IT, connected car and B2B marketing;</li><li>The chance to work in a fast moving, innovative and international team, dealing with all kind of different countries and cultures;</li><li>You will never get bored! We move fast like a “start-up” but have the benefits of a billion euro company;</li><li>A company culture that likes to work hard and play hard. We like to have fun. There is no sense coming to a job everyday if you don’t like the people you work with;</li><li>Decisive actions. We don’t like to wait. It’s in our DNA to move forward. So it only makes sense that we don’t jam the company with lots of layers. We make things happen. Quickly;</li><li>Flexible benefits, 25 annual leave days, flexible holiday plan, collective health insurance, pension scheme, up to 50% discount on products, bonus scheme.</li></ul><p></p><p><b>Who are we?</b></p><p></p><p>Founded in 1991 and headquartered in Amsterdam, we have 4,100 employees worldwide and sell our products in over 36 countries. Our business consists of four customer facing business units: Consumer, Automotive, Licensing and Telematics.</p><p></p><p>TomTom Telematics is a Business Unit of TomTom dedicated to fleet management, vehicle telematics and connected car services. WEBFLEET is a Software-as-a-Service solution, used by small to large businesses to improve vehicle performance, save fuel, support drivers and increase overall fleet efficiency. In addition, TomTom Telematics provides services for the insurance, rental and leasing industries, car importers and companies that address businesses as well as consumers.</p><p></p><p>TomTom Telematics is one of the world’s leading telematics solution providers with more than 696,000 subscriptions worldwide. The company services drivers in more than 60 countries, giving them the industry’s strongest local support network and widest range of sector-specific third party applications and integrations. More than 46,000 customers benefit every day from the high standards of confidentiality, integrity and availability of our ISO/IEC 27001:2013 certified service, re-audited in November 2016.</p><p></p><p>For further information, please visit tomtom.com/telematics</p><p>Follow us on Twitter @TomTomWEBFLEET</p><p></p><p><b>Interested?</b></p><p></p><p>We would like to meet you!</p><p>Please click on the apply button or go to www.tomtom.com/careers</p><p>Pre-employment screening is part of the selection process.</p>",
