    "id": "Social-Media-Intern---Employer-Brand_JR0000141-8",
    "title": "Social Media Intern - Employer Brand",
    "description": "<p>You love telling stories, yet a limited amount of characters does not scare you.</p><p>You’re creative, quick and concise, always keeping a sharp eye for detail.</p><p>Your content is often consumed on the go, but the feeling it conveys sticks.</p><p>You’re always on the hunt for new trends, knowing what’s hot... and what’s not.</p><p>You live and breathe social media. And now it’s time to get rewarded for it.</p><p>You’d love to join a team whose primary purpose is to celebrate people and culture (and there is a lot to celebrate).</p><p>Does this sound like you?<br>Then apply for our Social Media internship!</p><p></p><p>As the Employer Brand team at a leading technology company, we are looking for someone who is passionate about both technology and people — someone who thrives in a fast-paced environment; who is not afraid to seek answers and ask questions if they can’t be found; who can manage his/her time and always has ideas to fill a content calendar, but also has a knack for creating appealing content on the fly; who understands that different audiences call for different messages, tones of voices and visuals; and who knows that analytics don’t lie.</p><p>In a nutshell, your missions will revolve around:</p><ul><li><b>Creating &amp; curating social content to drive awareness and consideration among potential candidates.</b></li><li>Developing a social media strategy to support Employer Brand's objectives.&nbsp;</li><li>Actively interacting with TomTom employees, stakeholders and candidates.</li><li>Measuring social media campaign effectiveness and creating weekly reports.</li></ul><p></p><p>You also don’t need to be a poet or a recognised author, but you do need to be a master of the English language (<b>native or fluent in English</b>). You will have to work with stakeholders from our (57) offices around the world, being able to clearly communicate with and understand others.&nbsp;</p><p></p><p>You don’t need 10 years of experience for this role. With the right attitude and willingness to learn, we will give you the right tools to succeed.&nbsp;</p><p>So in three words (again limited amount of characters), we are looking for someone who is: proactive, creative, organized.<br>If this is you, we’d love to hear from you!</p><p></p><p>You should only apply if you are an EU citizen due to working permit regulations.</p><p><span><b>Interested?</b></span></p><p><span>For the full story about the vacancy or procedure, please click on the apply button, and go to http//tomtom.com/careers</span></p>",
