    "description": "<p>Our team <b>achieves more</b> every day. So can you.</p><p></p><p>TomTom is navigation and more: wearable technology, action cameras, mobile applications, portable navigation devices, automotive components, fleet management systems, location technology products, real-time traffic, map information and navigation services. In the Travel Service department we develop award-winning services which get everyone where they need to be faster, more reliably, on time and safely.</p><p>At TomTom you can develop your skills in all fields of software engineering, from the UI down to the data layer. In our team you will focus primarily on server-side applications based on Java, but also work on user interfaces. We develop products used by internal and external customers; we build them, we run them and we maintain them. Some of the applications deal with huge amounts of data, while others focus on fast processing.</p><p></p><p>We have been making navigation apps since 2002 and have been the market leader ever since.</p><p>And, we are not slowing down.</p><ul><li>Do you like making complex situations more visible?</li><li>Do you refer to yourself as the Master of Java and Algorithms?</li><li>Do you like working on next generation technologies? Who doesn’t actually?</li><li>What about making a difference with your OWN ideas for features and improvements, getting a top place on the backlog?</li></ul><p></p><p><b>Sound interesting?</b></p><p></p><p>How about - <b>Want to code the future?</b></p><p>Pretty big thinking. We like to think we make that happen.</p><p>We are looking for the best Java developers who have a passion for building applications that drive the future of navigation and beyond. Designing and developing the best possible products is in our DNA.</p><p></p><p><b>Here’s a little taste of your challenge</b></p><ul><li>Provide drivers with relevant and complex information at a glance by creating comprehensive algorithms</li><li>Improve the driver’s experience by generating new software components to deliver even more complete information</li><li>Create highly scalable and high performing solutions, able to be running on all sorts of hardware</li><li>Designing, implementing, testing and maintaining strategic feature development in J2EE projects.</li><li>Improving the non-functional system characteristics of our backends and frontends, focusing on response times and uptime.</li><li>Finding solutions to decrease time-to-market in tight collaboration with our devops team.</li><li>Continuously improving our testing and integration strategies.</li></ul><p></p><p></p><p><b>What we expect from you</b></p><p></p><ul><li>Master of server side Java development in a Linux environment.</li><li>You make your Scrum team better every day.</li><li>Solid knowledge of distributed and scalable systems.</li><li>You are able to define and implement well defined REST services.</li><li>Expertise in software development for scalable Linux systems with strict availability and performance requirements.</li><li>You like working with others and help them to achieve more.</li><li>Familiarity with Puppet, KVM, Docker, Ruby, Python, monitoring are a plus</li><li>Outside-the-box thinking and the ability to bring new ideas to the table.</li></ul><p></p><p></p><p><b>What you can expect from us</b></p><ul><li>You will never get bored!&nbsp; We move fast like a “start-up” but have the benefits of a billion euro company.</li><li>A company culture that likes to work hard and play hard.&nbsp; We like to have fun.&nbsp; There is no sense coming to a job everyday if you don’t like the people you work with.</li><li>Have an idea? A suggestion? A new way of doing something?&nbsp; The founders are still very present in the company and are very accessible.&nbsp; We all are.&nbsp; There is always room for good ideas.&nbsp; Entrepreneurialism is valued.</li><li>Decisive actions. &nbsp;We don’t like to wait.&nbsp; It’s in our DNA to move forward.&nbsp; So it only makes sense that we don’t jam the company with lots of layers.&nbsp; We make things happen.&nbsp; Quickly.</li><li>Berlin.&nbsp; A pretty cool city to live and work. Lots of inspiration and when it’s sunny, the whole city comes alive!</li></ul><p></p><p><b>Want to join us?</b></p><p><i>We would like to meet you!</i></p><p>We kindly ask you to complete the form and attachments in English.</p><p>Pre-employment screening of all external candidates is part of the selection process.</p>",
