    "id": "Backend-Software-Engineer---Telematics_25428-12",
    "title": "Backend Software Engineer - Telematics",
    "description": "<p><b><i>‘Fleet management services is one of the hottest and fastest growth areas in the car services industry at this moment and it is our challenge to outperform the market at any moment.’</i></b><i><span>&nbsp;</span>&nbsp;Thomas Schmidt, MD TomTom Telematics.</i></p><p>TomTom Telematics is the fastest growing business unit within TomTom. It’s main SaaS platform WEBFLEET supports over 46.000 business customers worldwide to realize substantial operational performance improvement. With a strategy of indirect and direct sales as well as M&amp;A, TomTom Telematics grows with more than 30% yearly. Would you like to be part of a team that challenges itself to outperform daily and contribute to growing a new (SaaS for Business) market?</p><p>Where do you want to be…in a year, in 5 years?<br>What if you had the opportunity to achieve more in less time then you could ever imagine?<br><br>At TomTom, you can.&nbsp;</p><p>We are looking for the best and brightest minds in&nbsp;<b>SaaS</b>&nbsp;<b>backend&nbsp;developmen</b>t for our team in&nbsp;<b>Barcelona.</b>&nbsp;Be part of an agile cross-functional team that works on both graphical user interfaces and their connected applications on server side. The code base consists mainly of Java, HTML, JavaScript and some Flex/Flash, GWT, Groovy etc. Together with a team of highly skilled and motivated individuals, you will:<br>&nbsp;</p><p><b>Sound good so far?</b>&nbsp;<br><br>Here’s a little taste of your challenge:</p><ul><li>Find and refine requirements, discuss new features and collaborate with product managers</li><li>Agree the technical implementation with involved component owners WEBFLEET architects and estimate its work effort</li><li>Implement, test and demonstrate new product features following agile best practices</li><li>Work on further usability or performance improvements and bug fixes<br>&nbsp;</li></ul><p><b>What we are looking for:</b></p><ul><li>You have a graduate degree on computing or engineering, with 3 to 5 years of experience in software development.</li><li>You need to be able to master the fine arts of software engineering as e.g. design for quality and reuse, componentization, resilience and multi-threading and at the same you should be willing to get your hands dirty and dive deep into all any kind of problem that comes your way.</li><li>You are fluent in English (written and spoken).</li><li>You are a great communicator, analytic, goal-oriented, quality-focused, yet still agile person who likes to work with software engineers; you will interact a lot with other developers, component owners, UX engineers and system engineers.</li><li>You have xxperience in Java server-side development, including Spring and Hibernate/JPA and SQL.&nbsp;</li><li>We work in cross-functional teams, so it will be useful to have a variety of experience and technical interests as you may come across assignments that involve front-end development (e.g. with HTML5, JavaScript, CSS3, Angular.js, Flex, ActionScript), or scripting in various languages (e.g. Python, Groovy, etc.).<br>&nbsp;</li></ul><p><b>What you can expect:</b></p><ul><li>An adventure in software product development within a rapidly growing business unit of a globally renowned brand and various opportunities for your professional development.</li><li>Being part of a team of expert developers and contribute in building and adapting technology for WEBFLEET, TomTom’s leading fleet management system.<br>&nbsp;</li></ul><p><b>Let’s not forget the good stuff&nbsp;</b></p><ul><li>Competitive base salary with a generous commission scheme</li><li>Private health insurance (including children and partners)</li><li>Pension Plan (after 6 months contract)</li><li>Lunch Vouchers</li><li>50% discount on purchase of TomTom products;</li><li>The chance to work in a fast moving, innovative and international environment, dealing with all kind of different countries and cultures.<br>&nbsp;</li></ul><p><b>Want to join us?</b></p><p>We would like to meet you!</p><p>For the full story about the vacancy or procedure, please click on&nbsp;tomtom.com/careers</p><p>Pre-employment screening is part of the selection process.&nbsp;</p>",
