    "id": "Associate-Manager-Maps_JR0000239-2",
    "title": "Associate Manager Maps",
    "description": "<p><span>Are you looking for the next great challenge in your career and are you ready to join our world-class team of leaders? Are you looking for a job where you are fully responsible for Managing an activity, promoting state-of-the-art technology and a world-class brand? Then this might be the perfect opportunity for you!</span></p><p></p><p><span>The heart of location services is the map and TomTom delivers the most current digital map of the world. Since 2006 TomTom has collected anonymous GPS measurements from its users. This unique community harvests knowledge from local experts and it is combined with traditional sources including paper maps, field surveys, aerial and satellite imagery and mobile mapping vans. The result is a dynamic map full of enhanced content ranging from points of interest to 3D city maps.</span></p><p></p><p><span>The Sensor Sourcing Operations team provides the MAPS Product Units with word class source material and services. </span></p><p><span>We are taking care of:</span></p><ul><li><span>Mobile mapping: data collection worldwide, intake, technology improvement</span></li><li><span>Imagery acquisition and management</span></li><li><span>xFCD (car sensor data)</span></li><li><span>Mobile Mapping Light</span></li></ul><p></p><p><span><b>Sound interesting?</b></span></p><p></p><p><b>Here’s a little taste of your challenge:</b></p><ul><li><span>Manage a small team of professionals focused at delivering the following services:</span></li><li><span>Project management of key improvement project across SSO</span></li><li><span>Metrics management and follow up</span></li><li><span>Engineering backlog management (priority setting based on business value, user story creation, etc…)</span></li><li><span>Storage management of a server farm hosting 7+ PB of data</span></li><li><span>Personally manage some key projects</span></li><li><span>Be part of the SSO management team</span></li><li><span>Helping on structuring and solidifying the management practices of the team.</span></li></ul><p></p><p><span><b>&nbsp;What we expect from you:</b></span></p><ul><li><span>Fluent English</span></li><li><span>Bachelor degree (Master degree preferred) in either IT, GIS or Management with keen interest in computers and technology</span></li><li><span>Experience in project management and planning</span></li><li><span>Excellent analysis skills, at ease with data manipulation</span></li><li><span>Excellent communication skills</span></li><li><span>Knowledge of process improvement</span></li><li><span>Prior team management experience</span></li></ul><p></p><p><span><b>What you can expect from us</b></span></p><ul><li><span>You will never get bored!&nbsp; We move fast like a </span><span>“start-up</span>” but have the benefits of a billion euro company.</li><li><span>A company culture that likes to work hard and play hard. We like to have fun. There is no sense coming to a job everyday if you don</span><span>’t like the people you work with.</span></li><li><span>Have an idea? A suggestion? A new way of doing something? The founders are still very present in the company and are very accessible. We all are. There is always room for good ideas. Entrepreneurialism is valued.</span></li><li><span>Decisive actions. We don</span><span>’t like to wait.&nbsp;It</span>’s in our DNA to move forward.&nbsp; So it only makes sense that we don’t jam the company with lots of layers. We make things happen. Quickly.</li><li><span>Let</span><span>’s not forget the good stuff: flexible benefits (including multisport card), private medical care, 50% product discount and bonus scheme.</span></li><li><span>Łódź, a pretty cool city to live and work. Lots of inspiration and when it</span><span>’s sunny, the whole city comes alive!</span></li></ul><p></p><p><span><b>Want to join us?</b></span></p><p><span><b>We would like to meet you!</b></span></p><p><span>Please apply through www.tomtom.com/careers.</span></p><p><span>Your recruiter for this job is Karolina Leoniak.</span></p><p><span>We kindly ask you to complete the form and attachments in English.</span></p><p><span>Pre-employment screening of all external candidates is part of the selection process.</span></p><p></p>",
