    "title": "Technology Deployment Manager Eastern Europe & Central Asia",
    "description": "<p><b><i>“We create leading, fresh and accurate map content for Eastern Europe and Central Asia which enables our customers to keep moving and reaching their goals in an easy and smart way. Our content is easily accessible, continuously available, dynamic and it delivers compelling new value that drives product differentiation and competitive advantage.” Georg Fisch - Director Sourcing Operations.</i></b></p><p></p><p>Would you like to take a leading role in state-of-the-art technology implementation for digital mapping? Do you want to be able to influence the operations international teams and to continuously migrate to newer and better tools and processes?</p><p></p><p><b>Here’s a little taste of your challenge</b></p><p>We are looking for the best and brightest mind for the position Technology Deployment Manager for Eastern Europe &amp; Central Asia. The experience and future opportunities will include implementing the sourcing technical environment (tools &amp; processes) and setting requirements as well as providing training and a helpdesk and operational support towards regional teams. Besides, you will be interfacing with technical product owners and sharing knowledge across regions, enabling a global network of technology experts and managing the QMS within Region.</p><p>As a member of the regional team, you are asked to deliver the following:</p><ul><li>Ensure that deployment of TomTom technology in the region applies the most recent state-of-the-art production environment;</li><li>Manage the training requirements and training execution to make sure that all operations are done by qualified teams;</li><li>Lead and coach team, including planning &amp; prioritization, follow up on technology projects, guidance in problem cases;</li><li>Focus the region on innovation and adoption (top-down and bottom-up) to make sure that the region maintains a leading role;</li><li>Ensure that regional organization is acting in line with corporate and departmental QMS-standards;</li><li>Be custodian of the regional content quality, focused on absolute and relative quality (benchmarking).<p><b>What do we expect from you?</b></p><p>There is no set route to become a Technology Deployment Manager at TomTom. But to be successful in this role, this is the kind of profile we have in mind:</p></li><li>5+ years’ experience managing complex, highly visible technical projects;</li><li>College or University Degree;</li><li>GIS Software and MS Office Software knowledge;</li><li>Intercultural Communication Skills to do Change Management;</li><li>In depth knowledge on TomTom products, customer requirements, data specifications and production tools;<p><b>What you can expect from us</b></p></li></ul><ul><li>You will never get bored!&nbsp; We move fast like a “start-up” but have the benefits of a billion euro company.</li><li>A company culture that likes to work hard and play hard.&nbsp; We like to have fun.&nbsp; There is no sense coming to a job everyday if you don’t like the people you work with.</li><li>Have an idea? A suggestion? A new way of doing something?&nbsp; The founders are still very present in the company and are very accessible. We all are. There is always room for good ideas. Entrepreneurialism is valued.</li><li>Decisive actions. We don’t like to wait.&nbsp;It’s in our DNA to move forward.&nbsp; So it only makes sense that we don’t jam the company with lots of layers.&nbsp; We make things happen. Quickly.</li></ul><p><b>Want to join us?</b></p><p><i>We would like to meet you!</i></p><p>We kindly ask you to complete the form and attachments in English.</p><p>Pre-employment screening of all external candidates is part of the selection process.</p><p></p><p><b>Who are we?</b></p><p>Founded in 1991 and headquartered in Amsterdam, we have 4,700 employees worldwide and sell our products in over 36 countries.</p><p>TomTom empowers movement. Every day millions of people around the world depend on TomTom to make smarter decisions. We design and develop innovative products that make it easy for people to keep moving towards their goals.</p><p>Our map-based components include map content, online map-based services, real-time traffic, and navigation software. Our consumer products include PNDs, navigation apps, and GPS sports watches. Our main business products are custom in-dash navigation systems and a fleet management system, which is offered to fleet owners as an online service with integrated in-vehicle cellular devices.</p><p>Our business consists of four customer facing business units: Consumer, Automotive, Licensing and Telematics.</p><p>For further information, please visit <a href=\"http://www.tomtom.com/\" target=\"_blank\">www.tomtom.com</a></p><p></p><p><b>Interested?</b></p><p>For the full story about the vacancy or procedure, please click on <a href=\"http://www.tomtom.jobs/\" target=\"_blank\">www.tomtom.jobs</a> or contact Marta Brzeszczynska.</p><p></p>",
