    "id": "Sr-Test-Engineer_25606-6",
    "title": "Sr Test Engineer",
    "description": "<p>Our team&nbsp;<b>achieves more</b>&nbsp;every day. So can you.</p><p></p><p>At TomTom Automotive/Custom Systems we have been making built-in car navigation since 2008, introduced the connected car in 2010 and are a major player in the area of Highly Automated Driving. And, we are not slowing down.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><ul><li>Would you like to develop connected navigation products for the car industry that contribute to the FUTURE OF DRIVING?</li><li>Do you want to play a key role in bringing the latest innovation to automotive end users?&nbsp;</li><li>Do you want to be part of an Agile (Scrum, SAFe) and international working environment, allowing you to develop yourself?</li><li>What about being a part of a company pushing the envelope in HIGHLY AUTOMATED DRIVING</li></ul><p><br><b>Sound interesting?</b></p><p>We are looking for the brightest (Senior) Software Test Engineer to join our Automotive/Custom System Test Engineering team in Eindhoven.&nbsp;As a (Senior) Software Test Engineer within Custom Systems in Eindhoven, The Netherlands, the challenges are many. Our engineering processes are based on agile and scrum principles, where the distinction between test and development is becoming blurred. As a consequence we need someone who is familiar with the concepts and tools of Continuous Integration and is familiar with automating tests on (user) interface level.</p><p></p><p>You will work inside a scrum team and help this team in determining if their output is of sufficient quality to be released to the customer. Because our portfolio, and subsequently our platforms, are so varied (we have ‘custom’ in our name for a reason), our test landscape is extremely varied as well, and uses a multitude of tools. The ability to handle a steep learning curve and being able to choose the right test solutions are therefore highly valued.</p><p></p><p>We are looking for a (Senior) Software Tester, with emphasis on \"software\", to enable:</p><ul><li>Easy communication with our software engineers, also for knowledge sharing</li><li>Be able to support the software development effort when necessary (this is not the main focus, though)</li></ul><p></p><p>We have unit, component and interface tests, which for the most part run automatically as part of our build system, in a custom-made test framework.</p><p>Our interface tests are in Java and our products (implementations) and unit tests are usually in C++.</p><p></p><p><b>Responsibilities</b></p><p>The (Senior) Software tester takes the lead for the following topics. The final outcome is always a team responsibility.</p><ul><li>Define the test strategy</li><li>Define test/quality metrics</li><li>Facilitate test automation (note: main focus of the tester is on the design;&nbsp;the actual implementation work is shared with the team)</li><li>Keep an eye on the readability and complexity of the test code</li><li>Grow test awareness and knowledge within the team (coaching)</li></ul><p></p><p><b>Skills/knowledge</b></p><p>Must have:</p><ul><li>Fluent in written and spoken English</li><li>Communicative, team player</li><li>Experience with supporting embedded software development</li><li>Extensive knowledge of testing techniques (e.g. boundary value analysis, black/white box testing, etc) and is able to apply them creatively</li><li>Extensive knowledge of test automation and is able to design and implement an automated test setup and test cases</li><li>Working knowledge of Continuous Integration and our tooling:<ul><li>QuickBuild</li><li>Jenkins</li><li>Docker</li></ul></li><li>Working knowledge of Ubuntu Linux</li><li>Working knowledge of (i.e. being able to read) the main (programming) languages we use:<ul><li>C++</li><li>Java&nbsp;</li><li>Python</li><li>Gherkin</li></ul></li></ul><p></p><p>Nice to have:</p><ul><li>Knowledge of Scrum (practical experience would be a bonus)</li><li>Knowledge of technical aspects of coding (e.g. how to handle concurrent asynchronous calls)</li><li>ISTQB certification (CTFL, CTAL or CAT) would be preffered (at least to show some basic knowledge)</li><li>Knowledge of Automotive SPICE</li><li>Knowledge of software quality tooling: Protex/Blackduck, TIOBE TICS, etc.</li></ul><p></p><p><b>Want to join us and be part of the FUTURE OF DRIVING?</b><br><i>We would like to meet you!</i></p><p>Please apply through&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.tomtom.com/careers\" target=\"_blank\">www.tomtom.com/careers</a>. We kindly ask you to complete the form and attachments in English.<br><br>More info about TomTom Automotive can be found&nbsp;<a href=\"http://automotive.tomtom.com/en/connected-navigation-system?_ga=1.133545546.533444928.1452166059\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>.</p><p>A technical assessment and Pre-employment screening is part of the selection process.</p>",
