    "id": "Bid-Manager_JR0000137-1",
    "title": "Bid Manager",
    "description": "<p>Our team <b>achieves more</b> every day. So can you.</p><p></p><p>Where we’re going we don’t need steering wheels. At TomTom Automotive, we see the growth of automation and increase of connectivity as an opportunity to keep innovating and engage in new business areas.”&nbsp; Paul Hesen, VP Engineering TomTom Automotive. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p></p><p><b>Here’s a little taste of your challenge: </b></p><ul><li>Collaborate with Sales Directors to create content-rich, compelling and competitive commercial proposals in response to new Automotive customer opportunities.</li><li>Capture, standardize and document “best practices” and make them available to Sales Directors and Engineers. Examples include maintaining a library of content for tender responses, proposal templates</li><li>Coordinate the implementation of follow-up activities for newly won opportunities, such as negotiation of contracts in collaboration with Legal, organization of information flows e.g. new deal content to Financial Shared Service Center, calendar and preliminary data of expected future bids to Product Units</li></ul><p></p><p><b>What will you have to deliver?</b></p><ul><li>Customer proposals in response to OEM “Request for Proposals”. Coordinate the preparation of product briefs, pricing tables, legal terms and conditions and any other.</li><li>Deal Review support. Assist the Account Manager’s preparation for the Deal Review with MD and FD, requesting formal approval for the proposal. Anticipate and address potential blockers and discussion points.</li><li>Standardized deal descriptions, benchmark data and best practice descriptions in the Bid Office share points and Salesforce databases. Define and deliver training to the Sales organization on the bid process and available resources to assist them in proposal preparation.</li><li>Signed contractual agreements. In collaboration with Legal and the Account Manager, coordinate and/or negotiate agreements covering new deals, starting with newly won opportunities resulting in signed contracts fully reflecting the initially approved terms.</li><li>Maintain and upgrade standardized Bid Management process descriptions and best practices.</li></ul><p></p><p><b>What we expect from you: </b></p><ul><li>Commercially savvy: business acumen, common sense and interpersonal skills to practically apply this expertise to real world situations.</li><li>A successful Bid Manager has the mental agility to reconcile the often conflicting requirements of good Governance (minimizing the risks of the company), compelling commercial offerings (winning the business versus highly skilled and motivated competitors), and being easy to work with for our customer.</li><li>Strong personality, with natural ability to influence and work effectively with all hierarchical levels of an organization – both internally (e.g. aligning various stakeholders on common goals and activities) as externally (e.g. with customer Purchasing and Legal organizations to negotiate out legal agreements). Don’t take this lightly: frankly it’s not for everyone…</li><li>Bid Managers regularly find themselves in a situation of conflicting interests and tense emotions.</li><li>Self-starter with a passion for results. Has a sense of urgency, takes initiative and motivates people to contribute to a result. Is intrinsically motivated even when facing resistance</li><li>Conceptual thinker who can turn learnings into practical process changes. Able to capture best practices and use them to drive continuous improvements in the processes and software tools we use.</li><li>Ability to constantly learn and stay on top of changes in our technology, products and business models. Previous Bid Management experience or exposure to a complex environment is a plus.</li></ul><p></p><p><b>What do the best people in this role do differently than the average person?</b></p><ul><li>Bring people together and make them work effectively towards a common goal, through influencing in a multi-functional team setting as opposed to hierarchical settings.</li><li>Combine doing with improving. Is out there every day making it happen, but also takes a regular step back to reflect on and improve our ways of working.</li><li>Voraciously curious. Constantly learning about the business, products, personalities, customers, sales pitches…</li></ul><p></p><p><b>What you can expect from us</b></p><ul><li>Business growth in BU Automotive is fueled by winning new deals, and the Bid Manager is at the heart of the action!</li><li>We are constantly raising the bar on our internal capability to pitch for deals, and get a better grip on their implementation, delivery and risk management. As Automotive Bid Manager, you support our Sales organization in the preparation and implementation of new deals, enabling them to focus on the customer-centric activities.</li><li>You work closely with all internal stakeholders to coordinate bid preparation activities, ranging from product briefs for newly developed, customized products over pricing to legal terms and conditions.</li><li>The stakes are high, making this a demanding, impactful and highly visible role acting as a stepping stone to further commercial, financial or managerial career opportunities.</li></ul><p><br><b>Want to join us?</b></p><p><i>We would like to meet you!</i></p><p>We kindly ask you to complete the form and attachments in English.</p><p>Pre-employment screening of all external candidates is part of the selection process.</p>",
