    "id": "Full---Stack-Java-Software-Engineer_JR0000213-1",
    "title": "Full - Stack Java Software Engineer",
    "description": "<p>Our teams <b>achieve more</b> every day. So can you.</p><p></p><p>Do you want to contribute to the future of map making? Are you proficient in Java and not afraid to venture in other areas if the need arises? Are Artificial Intelligence, Machine Learning or Big Data not just buzzwords to you? Then you may be the All-round Software Engineer we’re looking for!</p><p></p><p><b>Here’s a little taste of your challenge</b></p><ul><li>Use Machine Learning to discover map updates hidden in terabyte sized daily data feeds</li><li>Automate transactional map to transform TomTom's map data into a Real time Map</li><li>Apply deep learning (deeplearning4j) to further automate TomToms transactional mapmaking allowing faster and more accurate detection of real world changes</li><li>Building new and more productive solutions from start to end - you'll have to deliver not just software tools but complete end-to-end processes</li></ul><p></p><p><b>What do we expect from you?</b></p><ul><li>Master’s degree in computer science or equivalent</li><li>Profound knowledge of the Java universe</li><li>Good knowledge of design patterns and clean code principles</li><li>Eager to learn, able to get acquainted with a broad range of technologies and a diverse software stack in a short timeframe</li><li>Focus on ‘getting things done’, without sacrificing quality</li><li>Fluent in English</li><li>Hands-on experience in any of the below is a plus</li><li>Big Data (HBase on Hadoop)</li><li>Geospatial processing</li><li>Machine learning</li><li>Artificial Intelligence</li><li>Remote Sensing</li></ul><p></p><p><b>What is in it for you?</b></p><ul><li>A challenging job in a world-class international company promoting innovative and modern technologies in the field of digital mapping, traffic and navigation solutions</li><li>An opportunity to work in a dynamic team, with a mixture of cultures and nationalities</li><li>Plenty of room for personal growth, in any direction you choose</li><li>Market rate salary, bonuses and benefits</li><li>A company culture that encourages you to work hard and play hard. We like to have fun!</li></ul><p></p><p><b>Want to join us?</b></p><p><i>We would like to meet you!</i></p><p>We kindly ask you to complete the form and attachments in English.</p><p>Pre-employment screening of all external candidates is part of the selection process.</p>",
