    "id": "Mobile-Developer---Telematics_25404-10",
    "title": "Mobile Developer - Telematics",
    "description": "<p><b>“Would you like to see your work operated by hundreds of thousands of customers on a daily base?”</b></p><p><b><i>Michael Suess, VP Engineering, TomTom Telematics</i></b></p><p>TomTom Telematics is the fastest growing Business Unit of TomTom, and one of the world’s leading providers of fleet management solutions and professional telematics services, delivered as “Software-as-a-Service (SaaS)”. Our products are designed to help professional drivers to drive greener, safer and more efficiently. Our award winning online platform, WEBFLEET, is highly scalable and has the highest standards in terms of reliability and security. TomTom Telematics services more than 46,000 fleet customers in 25 countries with more than 700,000 active monitored units/vehicles and is Europe’s largest and fastest growing fleet management service provider.<br>&nbsp;</p><p>Where do you want to be…in a year, in 5 years?<br>What if you had the opportunity to achieve more in less time then you could ever imagine?<br><br>At TomTom, you can.&nbsp;To further accelerate our growth even more and strengthening our leading position we are on the outlook for a <b>Mobile Developer.</b></p><p>We are looking for talented people who are passionate about great products and agile practices. Be part of an agile cross-functional team and work on mobile applications for iOS and Android as well as their server-side backend. Bigger parts of the code base are currently in Xamarin, something you should be comfortable with.</p><p><b>Sound good so far?</b></p><p>Here’s a little taste of your challenge:</p><ul><li>Discuss new features and collaborate with the development and UX team, commercial product manager and product owner.</li><li>Specify technical implementation with component owners and estimate the effort.</li><li>Implement, test and demonstrate new product features in an agile process.</li><li>Work on usability, quality, and performance improvements including bug fixes.<br>&nbsp;</li></ul><p><b>What do we expect from you?</b><br>&nbsp;</p><p>There is no set route to become a <b>Mobile developer </b>at TomTom. But to be successful in this role, this is the kind of profile we have in mind:</p><ul><li>You have a degree in computer science or similar.</li><li>You are a great communicator, analytic, goal-oriented, quality-focused, yet still agile person; you will interact a lot with UX engineers, other developers, component owners and system engineers.</li><li>You have a clear overview about all layers in computer software development.</li><li>You have development experience in these areas: Java, Android and iOS</li><li>Alternatively you are an experienced Java developer with an interest in gaining track in mobile development</li><li>You have good command of English.</li><li>The following experiences are a plus:<ul><li>Xamarin, C# or Spring</li><li>Modern Web technology</li><li>Test automation e.g. with Ranorex.</li></ul></li><li>Command of German or Spanish is a plus.<br>&nbsp;</li></ul><p><b>What can you expect:</b></p><ul><li>You will never get bored! We move fast like a “start-up” but have the benefits of a billion euro company</li><li>A company culture that likes to work hard and play hard. We like to have fun. There is no sense coming to a job everyday if you don’t like the people you work with.<br>&nbsp;</li></ul><p><b>Let’s not forget the good stuff&nbsp;</b></p><ul><li>Competitive base salary with a generous bonus scheme.</li><li>Private health insurance (including children and partners).</li><li>Pension Plan (after 6 months contract).</li><li>Lunch Vouchers.</li><li>50% discount on purchase of TomTom products.</li><li>The chance to work in a fast moving, innovative and international environment, dealing with all kind of different countries and cultures.<br>&nbsp;</li></ul><p><b>Want to join us?</b><br>&nbsp;</p><p>We would like to meet you!</p><p>For the full story about the vacancy or procedure, please click on&nbsp;tomtom.com/careers</p><p>Pre-employment screening is part of the selection process.&nbsp;</p>",
