    "id": "Full-Stack-Software-Engineer-Java---Telematics_JR0000320-1",
    "title": "Full-Stack Software Engineer Java - Telematics",
    "description": "<p><b><i>“Would you like to see your work operated by hundreds of thousands of customers on a daily base?”</i></b><i> <b>Michael Suess, VP Engineering, TomTom Telematics</b></i></p><p></p><p>TomTom Telematics is the fastest growing Business Unit of TomTom, and one of the world’s leading providers of fleet management solutions and professional telematics services, delivered as “Software-as-a-Service (SaaS)”. Our products are designed to help professional drivers to drive greener, safer and more efficiently. Our award winning online platform, WEBFLEET, is highly scalable and has the highest standards in terms of reliability and security. TomTom Telematics services more than 46,000 fleet customers in 36 countries with more than 700,000 active monitored units/vehicles and is Europe’s largest and fastest growing fleet management service provider.</p><p></p><p>Where do you want to be…in a year, in 5 years?</p><p></p><p>What if you had the opportunity to achieve more in less time then you could ever imagine?<br><br>At TomTom, you can.&nbsp;To further accelerate our growth even more and strengthening our leading position we are on the outlook for a <b>Full-stack Software Engineer.</b></p><p></p><p>We are looking for talented people who are passionate about great products and agile practices. Be part of an agile cross-functional team and work on graphical user interfaces and their connected applications on server side.</p><p></p><p><b>Sound good so far?</b></p><p></p><p>Here’s a little taste of your challenge:</p><ul><li>Discuss new features and collaborate with the development and UX team, commercial product manager and product owner;</li><li>Agree the technical implementation with involved component owners and estimate its work effort;</li><li>Implement, test and demonstrate new product features in an agile process;</li><li>Develop complete sets of functionality including the backend and user interfaces;</li><li>Work on further usability, performance improvements or quality assurance, including bug fixes and test automation.</li></ul><p></p><p><b>What do we expect from you?</b></p><p></p><p>There is no set route to become a <b>Full-Stack Software Engineer</b> at TomTom. But to be successful in this role, this is the kind of profile we have in mind:</p><ul><li>University degree in computer science or similar;</li><li>Very good German and English language skills;</li><li>You are a great communicator, analytic, goal-oriented, quality-focused, yet still agile person who likes to work with software engineers; you will interact a lot with UX engineers, other developers, component owners and system engineers;</li><li>Your clear overview about all layers in computer software development is impressive and having great knowledge about <b>REST APIs</b> and how to make and integrate them in products is your advantage;</li><li>You have frontend development experience in some of these areas: <b>HTML5</b>,<b> JavaScript</b>,<b> CSS3</b>,<b> React</b>,<b> Redux</b>,<b> SASS</b>;</li><li>Additionally you are experienced in Java server-side development, including lightweight <b>JEE</b>,<b> Spring</b>,<b> Hibernate</b>, using <b>SQL</b> and <b>noSQL data stores</b>.</li></ul><p></p><p><b>What do we offer? </b></p><p></p><p>An adventure in software product development within a rapidly growing business unit of a globally renowned brand. After getting started you will have various opportunities for your professional development. Being part of a team of expert developers and contribute in building and adapting technology for our Telematics service platform, TomTom’s leading fleet management system. Indefinite contract, 30 annual leave days, child care policy, 100% employer funded pension plan, up to 50% discount on products, 15% bonus scheme. Among others, an online learning platform (1500 courses &amp; 11000 e-books) as well as live speeches from software development gurus, like Uncle Bob.</p><p></p><p><b>Interested?</b></p><p></p><p>For the full story about the vacancy or procedure please click on <u>www.tomtom.com/careers</u> or for specific questions contact Jana Zaremba.</p><p></p><p>Online assessments and pre-employment screening are part of the selection process.</p>",
